<html>
<head>
<title>Department of State
</title>
</head>
<body>
<a name=#A> </a>
<a href = "http://gcrio.ciesin.org/"><img align = bottom src = "/gifs/gcrio-header.gif"></a><br>
<hr><br>
<p align=center>
<h1>Department of State</h1>
<p align=left>
<h2>Areas Of Global Change Research</h2>
<p align=left>
The US Congress has established that, in order to assure effective implementation and review of science and technology policy, "the Secretary of State shall have primary responsibility for coordination and oversight with respect to all international scientific and technological activities of the US Government involving foreign countries, international organizations, and international commissions."  Furthermore, Congress noted that "individuals and organizations concerned with science and technology should be consulted in the formulation, implementation, and evaluation of foreign policy."
<p align=left>
To carry out this intent of Congress, the US Department of State, through its Bureau of Oceans and International Environmental and Scientific Affairs (OES), has coordination and oversight responsibility for US Government participation in international bilateral and multilateral science programs (including the international dimension of USGCRP), for data and information management and exchange, and for negotiation of related international instruments and agreements.  The Department has established mechanisms for facilitating consultations with concerned individuals and organizations, both within and outside the US Government.
<p align=left>
<h2>Related Research</h2>
<p align=left>
No other research activities focus on the science of global environmental change.
<p align=left>
<h2>Access Points</h2>
<p align=left>
<dl>
<dt>Department of State Home Page	
<dd><a href="http://dosfan.lib.uic.edu/index.html">http://dosfan.lib.uic.edu/index.html</a>
<p align=center>
<a href="http://www.gcrio.org/">GCRIO Home Page</a>      |      <a href=#A>Top of This Page</a>      
