<HEAD>
<TITLE>What's New</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY background="/grey.gif" text="#00080">
<center><IMG  WIDTH=435 HEIGHT=52 SRC="whats_new.gif" alt="What's New"></center>
<p>

<!--BEGIN-NEW-ARTICLES-->
<dl>
<dt><a href="/articles/docs/bus_spF.html"><b>Business Sucession Plan</b></a><br>
<dd><a href="/articles/summaries/bus_spS.html"><IMG
 WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="/articles/summary.gif" alt="summary"></a>
<a href="/articles/docs/bus_spF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="/articles/article.gif"
alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="/articles/consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>Unfortunately, many closely held businesses are found lacking when it comes to succession plans. The lack of this type of plan is potentially disastrous. In order to protect oneself from the risk of not planning ahead, business owners should enter into buysell agreements. These agreements, when properly financed, can ensure that the family is taken care of and that the business thrives.<P>

<dt><a href="/articles/docs/espl_goalsF.html"><b>Estate Planning Goals</b></a>
<dd><a href="/articles/summaries/espl_goalsS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="/articles/summary.gif" alt="summary"></a>
<a href="/articles/docs/espl_goalsF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="/articles/article.gif" alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="/articles/consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>Estate planning is often put off by those who view it as too complicated. However, avoiding proper planning can lead to some severe consequences for one's family and heirs. One of the major problems resulting from poor planning is a lack of liquidity. However, with the help of an advisor and some powerful planning techniques, these potential dangers can be averted.<P>


</dl>
<!--END-NEW-ARTICLES-->

