<head>
<title>The Executive Advisors</title>
<!-- Changed by: Mark Rosenstein, 17-Jul-1996 -->
</head>
<body background="grey.gif" text="#000080">
<center><IMG  WIDTH=435 HEIGHT=52 SRC="FNEA.gif" alt="First New England Advisors"></center><P>

<H3>About First New England Advisors <i>(Corporate Sponsor)</i></H3>

<blockquote>
First New England Advisors, Inc. (FNEA) is a Boston based company
founded in 1975 which specializes in financial management for a broad
range of clients.  Our tradition of service, professionalism and
teamwork has allowed us to become one of the premiere financial
planning firms in the country.  Our aim is to help you work towards
your financial goals.<P>

FNEA is a Boston Stock Exchange member and an SEC Registered
Investment Advisory firm.

</blockquote><P>

<H3>About <a name="sheehan">Daniel D. Sheehan</a>, CFP <i>(Editor and Publisher)</i></H3>

<blockquote>

<IMG  WIDTH=128 HEIGHT=153 SRC="/bios/Sheehan.gif" align="left" hspace=6>

Daniel Sheehan is a principal of First New England Advisors, Inc., a
Boston Stock Exchange member and an SEC Registered Investment Advisory
firm.  Based in Boston, Dan specializes in estate, investment, retirement and charitable planning.<P>

Dan brings to his clients a diversified financial services background.
He focuses on the development of plans for business owners and
individuals concerned with the accumulation and preservation of
capital, retirement planning, tax reduction, in concert with
strategies for the reduction of estate taxes.  He works with pension
plan trustees assisting them to comply with the complex maze of ERISA
guidelines, and other trustees in meeting their fiduciary
responsibilities.  He advises non-profit organizations in the
management of their investment assets, and individual donors in how to
accomplish their goals<P>

Dan is an experienced public speaker and has addressed many public and
corporate groups, such as: Successful Money Management; Financial
Strategies for Successful Retirement; and Estate Planning seminars.
Some of the topics covered include financial and retirement planning, charitable and estate planning, money management and asset allocation.<P>

Dan was born and raised in Yonkers, New York, and received a Bachelor
of Business Administration in Finance from Iona College in 1966 and
served two years in the U.S. Navy.  A successful business owner before
entering the financial services world, he is a Certified Financial
Planner, a member of the National Association of Security Dealers
holding Series 7, Series 63 and Series 65 securities licenses, and is
an SEC Registered Investment Advisor.<P>

He is a member of the Institute of Certified Financial Planners, the
Planned Giving Group of New England, the National Committee on Planned
Giving, and the National Association of Renaissance Advisors.
Throughout his career he has been very active in civic and charitable
work with such organizations as: Boy Scouts of America, American
Legion, Chamber of Commerce, and Labour&eacute; Center of Boston.<P>

Dan and his wife of 24 years, Linda, live in Braintree, Massachusetts,
and are the parents of three children.<P>

</blockquote>


