<HEAD>
<TITLE>Charitable Planning</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Mark Rosenstein, 23-Oct-1995 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY background="/grey.gif" text="#000080">
<center><IMG  WIDTH=435 HEIGHT=52 SRC="charitable_planning.gif" alt="Charitable Planning"></center>
<p>

<dl>
<dt><a href="docs/charit_rollF.html"><b>Charitable Roll-Over</b></a>
<dd><a href="summaries/charit_rollS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="summary.gif" alt="summary"></a>
<a href="docs/charit_rollF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="article.gif" alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>Many people are interested in leaving a portion of their wealth to
charity. For those who are looking to increase the amount they can
afford to donate, as well as provide for family members, the
Charitable Remainder Trust might be exactly the right strategy to
use.<P>

</dl>

