<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Estate Planning</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Mark Rosenstein, 23-Oct-1995 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY background="/grey.gif" text="#000080">
<center><IMG  WIDTH=435 HEIGHT=52 SRC="estate_planning.gif" alt="Estate Planning"></center>
<p>

<dl>
<dt><a href="docs/family_estate_planF.html"><b>Does My Family Really Need An Estate Plan?</b></a><P>
<dd><a href="summaries/family_estate_planS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="summary.gif" alt="summary"></a>
<a href="docs/family_estate_planF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="article.gif" alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>Estate planning is a very important process which ensures that
estates are passed down to heirs as they were intended to be, with
minimal state control and taxes. There are a variety of ways to
protect an estate from government control and high taxes, and each
estate plan should be carefully considered to formulate the most
advantageous strategy.<P>

<dt><a href="docs/espl_goalsF.html"><b>Estate Planning Goals</b></a>
<dd><a href="summaries/espl_goalsS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="summary.gif" alt="summary"></a>
<a href="docs/espl_goalsF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="article.gif" alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>Estate planning is often put off by those who view it as too complicated. However, avoiding proper planning can lead to some severe consequences for one's family and heirs. One of the major problems resulting from poor planning is a lack of liquidity. However, with the help of an advisor and some powerful planning techniques, these potential dangers can be averted.<P>

<dt><a href="docs/power_giftF.html"><b>Power Gifting Techniques in Your Estate Plan</b></a> <img src="new.gif"><!-- 10/12/95 -->
<dd><a href="summaries/power_giftS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="summary.gif" alt="summary"></a>
<a href="docs/power_giftF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="article.gif" alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>Estate taxes are voluntary. If an individual chooses not to plan ahead, that individual may be choosing to pay over 50% in estate taxes. One of the most powerful techniques in avoiding these high taxes is through gifting. With the proper use, this transfer of assets will allow family members, as opposed to the government, to inherit an individual's estate.<p>

<dt><a href="docs/special_needsF.html"><b>Solutions for Parents of Special Needs Children</b></a>
<dd><a href="summaries/special_needsS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="summary.gif" alt="summary"></a>
<a href="docs/special_needsF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="article.gif" alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>Raising a special needs child is a responsibility which requires
serious dedication. Additionally, it also requires solid, sensible
planning. The options open to parents can best be understood and
utilized through the services of an estate lawyer and an insurance
agent. Together, these professionals can work to ensure the future
welfare of a special needs child.<P>

<dt><a href="docs/family_partnershipF.html"><b>The Family Limited Partnership</b></a><P>
<dd><a href="summaries/family_partnershipS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="summary.gif" alt="summary"></a>
<a href="docs/family_partnershipF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="article.gif" alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>Family limited partnerships are becoming a popular way for
affluent families to transfer wealth to the next generation. Such
partnerships minimize estate taxes and also afford a degree of asset
protection for the family as a whole.


</dl>

<p><hr size=4 width=80%>
<center><a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/navigation"><IMG  WIDTH=359 HEIGHT=63 SRC="/navigation.gif" ISMAP
border=0></a></center>

