<HEAD>
<TITLE>Financial Planning</TITLE>
<!-- Changed by: Mark Rosenstein, 27-Oct-1995 -->
</HEAD>
<BODY background="/grey.gif" text="#000080">
<center><IMG  WIDTH=435 HEIGHT=52 SRC="financial_planning.gif" alt="Financial Planning"></center>
<p>

<dl>
<dt><a href="docs/too_busyF.html"><b>Financial Fitness Check</b></a>
<dd><a href="summaries/too_busyS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="summary.gif" alt="summary"></a>
<a href="docs/too_busyF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="article.gif" alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>Most people do not have the time necessary to completely optimize
their financial situation. However, it is essential for everyone to
keep their priorities in sight, and allocate some time to financial
planning. By planning early enough, individuals will be much better
prepared, and can stay focused on the priorities, not their costs.<P>


<dt><a href="docs/plan_for_2ndF.html"><b>Planning for the Second Time
Around</b></a>
<dd><a href="summaries/plan_for_2ndS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="summary.gif" alt="summary"></a>
<a href="docs/plan_for_2ndF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="article.gif" alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>Although divorce is something that most people do not feel comfortable
thinking about when they enter into a marriage, the potential for it
always exists. It is important to understand the impact on financial
planning that a divorce and remarriage can have.<P>


</dl>

<p><hr size=4 width=80%>
