<HEAD>
<TITLE>Investment Management</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY background="/grey.gif" text="#000080">
<center><IMG  WIDTH=435 HEIGHT=52 SRC="investment_management.gif" alt="Investment Management"></center>
<p>

<dl>
<dt><a href="docs/inst_asset_class_mfF.html"><b>Institutional Asset Class Mutual Funds: A Low-Cost Alternative</b></a>
<dd><a href="summaries/inst_asset_class_mfS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="summary.gif"
alt="summary"></a>
<a href="docs/inst_asset_class_mfF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="article.gif"
alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>Financial planners are constantly attempting to identify ways
by which they can add substantial value to the investment portfolios
of clients. An often overlooked strategy is the utilization of
institutional asset class mutual funds. These large mutual funds
represent whole market segments of securities with similar risk
characteristics and can be used as effective tools to achieve
diversification. These funds, previously unavailable to the public,
are now accessible through certain security firms.<P>

<dt>
<a href="docs/variable_annuitiesF.html"><b>The Tax-Deferred Allure of Variable Annuities</b></a>
<dd><a href="summaries/variable_annuitiesS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="summary.gif"
alt="summary"></a>
<a href="docs/variable_annuitiesF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="article.gif"
alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>Variable annuities have become one of the most popular tax advantaged
investments for retirement. Variable annuities gain their advantage
over other investments through their flexibility and tax-deferring
options. Although strictly long-term in nature, this form of
investment is appealing, and justifiably so, to many investors.

</dl>

<p><hr size=4 width=80%>
<center><a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/navigation"><IMG  WIDTH=359 HEIGHT=63 SRC="/navigation.gif" ISMAP
border=0></a></center>

