<HEAD>
<TITLE>Retirement Planning</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY background="/grey.gif" text="#000080">
<center><IMG  WIDTH=435 HEIGHT=52 SRC="retirement_planning.gif" alt="Retirement Planning"></center>
<p>

<dl>

<dt><a href="docs/401k_bestbetF.html"><b>401(k) Plans: Your Best Bet
For Retirement and Tax Savings</b></a>
<dd><a href="summaries/401k_bestbetS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="summary.gif" alt="summary"></a>
<a href="docs/401k_bestbetF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="article.gif" alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>401(k) plans are quickly becoming the most popular way to save for
retirement. They offer individuals the ability to accumulate money for
retirement while systematically reducing the amount paid in taxes each
year.<P>

<dt><a href="docs/discret_rpF.html"><b>Discretionary Retirement Plans</b></a> <img src="new.gif"><!-- 10/12/95 -->
<dd><a href="summaries/discret_rpS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="summary.gif" alt="summary"></a>
<a href="docs/discret_rpF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="article.gif" alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>Non-qualified plans are often believed to be somehow inferior to qualified plans. However, the flexibility afforded by non-qualified plans offers a considerable advantage to investors.<P>

<dt><a href="docs/abc_plusF.html"><b>Introducing ABC Plus</b></a>
<dd><a href="summaries/abc_plusS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="summary.gif" alt="summary"></a>
<a href="docs/abc_plusF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="article.gif" alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>According to federal tax law, pension and profit-sharing plans may not
discriminate in favor of highly paid employees. However, by testing
based on average employee benefits, it is possible for employers to
select certain participants who are then provided with a higher
contribution rate.<P>

<dt><a href="docs/retire_plan_sixF.html"><b>Six Key Strategies for
Planning in Your Later Years</b></a>
<dd><a href="summaries/retire_plan_sixS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="summary.gif" alt="summary"></a>
<a href="docs/retire_plan_sixF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="article.gif" alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>Even though most people look forward to retirement, there is a
large percentage of the population which is financially unprepared for
retirement. In order to be properly prepared, an individual must
invest wisely, making sure to remain diversified. This, along with
knowledge of all the options available through pension plans,
insurance, and trusts, should insure a comfortable retirement.<P>

<dt><a href="docs/serpsF.html"><b>An Alternative to Non-Qualified SERPs</b></a>
<dd><a href="summaries/serpsS.html"><IMG  WIDTH=63 HEIGHT=20 SRC="summary.gif" alt="summary"></a>
<a href="docs/serpsF.html"><IMG  WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="article.gif" alt="article"></a>
<a href="/consulting.html"><IMG  WIDTH=47 HEIGHT=20 SRC="consult.gif" alt="consult"></a>
<br>Due to recent tax law changes and required participation,
qualified plans have become far less attractive. The popular
alternative, SERPs (Supplemental Executive Retirement Plans), has its
downsides as well. The solution to this problem can be found, however,
in an Executive Split Dollar Delayed Roll-Out Plan. This plan has a
number of advantages over the others including substantial retirement
income, security against the failure of the corporation, and complete
cost recovery.

</dl>

<p><hr size=4 width=80%>
<center><a href="/cgi-bin/imagemap/navigation"><IMG  WIDTH=359 HEIGHT=63 SRC="/navigation.gif" ISMAP
border=0></a></center>

