<html><head><title>Tax Planning: Beyond the Palm Trees -- Tax Havens and Estate Planning (Summary)</title></head><body>

<h2><IMG  WIDTH=39 HEIGHT=29 SRC="/icon.gif"> <i>Executive Summary</i></h2>
<h2>Tax Planning: Beyond the Palm Trees -- Tax Havens and Estate Planning</h2>

<h3>By <a href="/bios/henry.html">Vaughn W. Henry</a></h3>

Offshore trusts are frequently looked on merely as vehicles used by
criminals to hide their ill-gotten gains. However, this reputation is
undeserved. Offshore trusts offer a wide range of legitimate services
which can be very beneficial to the protection of an estate.<P>

Two of the principal reasons for establishing an offshore trust or
international business corporation are privacy and
confidentiality. Assets can be effectively protected from frivolous
law suits, thus reducing the extravagant risk of being a professional
in today's litigious society.<P>

If executed properly, a trust can insulate the beneficiaries from the
actions of others. However, an incorrectly established foreign trust
can cause more problems than it solves. Local off-shore advisors,
though knowledgeable about their own particular laws, may not be
familiar with US regulations. It is essential to choose a competent
trust company with US tax law experience, operating in English
speaking countries. These locations should have good accessibility,
long standing laws, and modern telecommunications.<P>

The second major concern is the investment used within the trust
portfolio. This is usually offset, to some degree, by
diversification. As investors seek higher returns on their
investments, though, this becomes a more important issue. Services
provided by private banking firms allow clients to structure business
and personal finances which are especially helpful in
multi-generational planning. Other opportunities which may present
themselves through a foreign trust are the ability to work in more
than one currency, use unregistered mutual funds, or purchase both
domestic and foreign securities. Since many investors are skeptical
about investing out of the US, offshore mutual funds have begun to
offer popular fund managers and familiar US stocks.<P>

Since US trusts are prohibited from acting in perpetuity, many people
are turning towards international trusts. Besides protecting assets, a
well designed plan may eliminate some taxes as well as providing for
deferred earnings. However, as with any financial planning, a
competent and experienced team of advisors should be consulted. <P>

<a href="/articles/docs/beyond_palmF.html"><IMG
 WIDTH=46 HEIGHT=20 SRC="/articles/article.gif" alt="article"></a>

<a href="/articles/tax_planning.html"><IMG
 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=20 SRC="/articles/abstracts.gif" alt="abstracts"></a><p>

