erator forthe Olkiluoto Nuclear Power Station in Finland.</I><BR CLEAR="ALL"></P><P><IMG SRC="freepics/nyhetspics/gen2.gif" WIDTH="84" HEIGHT="85" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3">ABB Generation exporterar vattenkraftstationertill m&aring;nga l&auml;nder. Montage av en ABB-<A HREF="freepics/nyhetspics/gen2.jpg">generator</A>i Mrica vattenkraftstation, Indonesien.<BR><I>One example of many export deliveries from ABB Generation. Hydro Powergenerators under erection in Mrica Hydro Power station, Indonesia.</I><BRCLEAR="ALL"><HR ALIGN=LEFT><BR><B><A HREF="http://www.Adtranz.com/">Adtranz</A></B></P><P><IMG SRC="freepics/nyhetspics/tra5.gif" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="50" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0">For non-electrified rail lines Adtranz buildsone of the world's most environmentally - friendly diesel-powered trains.The <A HREF="freepics/nyhetspics/tra5.jpg">&quot;Kustpilen&quot;</A> trainin southern Sweden is a great success, and the train is being introducedon other Swedish regional lines as well.<BR CLEAR="ALL"></P><P><IMG SRC="freepics/nyhetspics/tra2.gif" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="56" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3">Adtranz High-Speed Tilting <A HREF="freepics/nyhetspics/tra2.jpg">X2000</A>cuts travel time by up to 30% on existing tracks, attracting more and morepeople to the railway. The train has shown very high technical reliability,which has resulted in minimum of maintenance and low operating costs.<BRCLEAR="ALL"></P><P><IMG SRC="freepics/nyhetspics/tra3.gif" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="37" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><A HREF="freepics/nyhetspics/tra3.jpg">Vagn 2000</A>is the new metro car for Stockholm Transport (SL) Sweden. It si designedwith the passenger in mind and vehicles' entire life-cycle cost and environmentalimpact hve been considered, resulting in low energy consumption and highdegree of recyclable materials throughout.<BR CLEAR="ALL"></P><P><IMG SRC="freepics/nyhetspics/tra1.gif" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="39" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0">The Izmir Light Rail Vehicle (LRV) is taylor-madefor the Izmir Light Rail Transit System, Turkey. It is based on Adtranz'years of experience in the field of Mass Transit, but with state-of-the-arttechnology.<BR CLEAR="ALL"></P><P><IMG SRC="freepics/nyhetspics/tra4.gif" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="57" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3">Adtranz's <A HREF="freepics/nyhetspics/tra4.jpg">newhigh-speed multiple unit</A> will begin revenue service between Oslo andNorway's new Gardemoen airport in 1998. The comfortable and quite 210 km/htrains are projected to attract half of the future travellers to the airport.<BRCLEAR="ALL"><HR ALIGN=LEFT><BR><B><A HREF="http://www.abb.se/crc/crc.html">ABB Corporate Research</A></B><BR><BR><IMG SRC="freepics/nyhetspics/crc1.gif" WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="58" ALIGN="LEFT"NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><A HREF="freepics/nyhetspics/crc1.jpg">Experimentuppst&auml;llning</A>f&ouml;r HVDC-isolation med luft.<BR><BR CLEAR="ALL"></P><P><BR><A HREF="freepics/nyhetspics/crc2.jpg"><IMG SRC="freepics/nyhetspics/crc2.gif"WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="58" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="0"></A>Atts&auml;kerst&auml;lla l&aring;ngtidsegenskaperna hos nya konstruktionsmateriali nyckelkomponenter &auml;r viktigt f&ouml;r att s&auml;kra p&aring;litligdrift och h&ouml;g tillg&auml;nglighet i ABB:s system.<BR><I>Evaluation of long term properties of new structual materials in keycomponenets is important to ensure reliable operation and high availabilityof ABB:s systems.</I><BR CLEAR="ALL"><HR ALIGN=LEFT><BR><B>TRC</B></P><P><A HREF="freepics/nyhetspics/trc1.jpg"><IMG SRC="freepics/nyhetspics/trc1.gif"WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="55" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" BORDER="0"></A>Enstor tillg&aring;ng f&ouml;r TRC &auml;r att man disponerar en test- ochservicehall f&ouml;r aktiv utrustning d&auml;r man kan ta in mycket storam&auml;triggar. P&aring; bilden kontrollerar Carl Bj&ouml;rkman och MarikaWestman en MINISESAM-rigg i servicehallen.<BR CLEAR="ALL"><HR ALIGN=LEFT><BR><B><A HREF="http://www.abb.se/atomweb/atomweb.htm">ABB Atom</A></B></P><P><A HREF="freepics/nyhetspics/ato1.jpg"><IMG SRC="freepics/nyhetspics/ato1.gif"WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="58" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="0"></A>Kutsarnakontrolleras visuellt.</P><P>&nbsp;</P><P><BR CLEAR="ALL"><BR><A HREF="freepics/nyhetspics/ato2.jpg"><IMG SRC="freepics/nyhetspics/ato2.gif"WIDTH="85" HEIGHT="58" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" BORDER="0"></A>Br&auml;nslestavarfylls automatiskt men UO<FONT SIZE=-2>2 </FONT>- kutsar med olika anriktningari axiella zoner<BR CLEAR="ALL"><HR ALIGN=LEFT><BR><B>ABB Industrial Systems</B></P><P><IMG SRC="freepics/nyhetspics/isy1.gif" WIDTH="57" HEIGHT="80" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><A HREF="freepics/nyhetspics/isy1.jpg">Port ofSingapore</A>, PSA. Tanjong Pagar Terminal en av de tre terminaler f&ouml;rvilka ABB levererat driv- och kontrollutrustning f&ouml;r containerkranar</TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></P><P><CENTER><HR WIDTH="200"><A HREF="ABBHOME.HTM"><IMG SRC="home.gif" BORDER="0" WIDTH="43" HEIGHT="30" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A></CENTER></BODY></HTML>␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀
