<TITLE>ABB Power Genaration</TITLE>
<head><body bgcolor=#ffffff  link=#000ac5 vlink=#3a3f61 alink=#747474 text=000000# BACKGROUND="paper.gif">
<Basefont size=3>
<img src="logo.gif" vspace=12 hspace=10 align=right >
<br clear=all>
</head><br>
<img src="redline.gif"><p>
<center><img vspace=10 src="Powergen.gif" alt=""></center><p>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="ABBJPG/POWGEN.JPG" HEIGHT=120 alt=""></CENTER>

<BLOCKQUOTE><font size=+ 0>The Swedish companies in the Power Generation segment can meet practically all the needs of power utilities and industry for efficient power generation and service. The segment's operations cover equipment, systems and plants for most primary energy sources such as water, coal, oil, natural gas and uranium, and renewable energy sources like wind and biomass.<P>
 
ABB in Sweden has a strong position in nuclear power technology. It also develops and supplies nuclear fuel, which has aroused great international interest. In Sweden, ABB also develops, manufactures and supplies generators and control equipment for hydro power plants, and turbo-generators, and undertakes turnkey hydro power projects.<P>

ABB ranks among the leading suppliers of gas and steam turbines as well as of combined-cycle power plants. In Sweden, ABB has also developed the clean and efficient coal technology PFBC.<P>

The segment also manufactures and markets flue gas cleaning systems and electrostatic precipitators for the efficient removal of dust particles and pollutants from industrial processes and power plants</font size=+1></BLOCKQUOTE><P>
&nbsp<P>
 
<center>
<table border=3 cellpadding=4 cellspacing=4>
