<TITLE>ABB Power Transmission and >Distribution</TITLE>
<head><body bgcolor=#ffffff  link=#000ac5 vlink=#3a3f61 alink=#747474 text=000000# BACKGROUND="paper.gif">
<Basefont size=3>
<img src="logo.gif" vspace=12 hspace=10 align=right >
<br clear=all>
</head><br>
<img src="redline.gif"><p>
<center><img vspace=10 src="Powertrans.gif" alt=""></center><p>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="ABBJPG/TRANDIST.JPG" HEIGHT=120 alt=""></CENTER>

<BLOCKQUOTE><font size=+0>The ABB Group's international power transmission centre is situated in Ludvika, which is also the main location of the Swedish ABB's Power Transmission and Distribution segment. The different companies in the segment develop, manufacture and market a wide range of products and systems, plants and services for power transmission and distribution. Several of the Swedish ABB companies have global responsibility in the ABB Group for their respective activities.<P>

The Swedish ABB is a leader in technologies for both high-voltage DC (HVDC) transmission and reactive power compensation (RPC).<P>

The great breadth of the segment allows ABB to offer customers different packages and turnkey deliveries. At the same time, ABB can undertake fast deliveries of smaller systems and individual products. The segment can also benefit from STRI, Swedish Transmission Research Institute, in Ludvika. STRI is a joint research centre established by ABB, Vattenfall and Svenska Kraftn&auml;t 
for the long-term development of the important power transmission technology.</font size=+1></BLOCKQUOTE><P>
&nbsp<P>
 
<center>
<table border=3 cellpadding=4 cellspacing=4>
		<tr><td align=left width=140></td>
			<td align=center width=65>ABB Group</td>
			<td align=center width=65>ABB Sweden</td>

		<tr><td align=left width=140>Revenues 1995 MSEK</td>
			<td align=right width=65>57 904</td>
			<td align=right width=65>13 289</td>

		<tr><td align=left width=140>Employees</td>
			<td align=right width=65>46 827</td>
			<td align=right width=65>5 718</td>
</table></center>
&nbsp<P>

