<TITLE>ABB Financial Services</TITLE>
<head><body bgcolor=#ffffff  link=#000ac5 vlink=#3a3f61 alink=#747474 text=000000# BACKGROUND="paper.gif">
<Basefont size=3>
<img src="logo.gif" vspace=12 hspace=10 align=right >
<br clear=all>
</head><br>
<img src="redline.gif"><p>
<center><img vspace=10 src="Finance.gif" alt=""></center><p>

<CENTER><IMG SRC="ABBJPG/FINANS.JPG" HEIGHT=120 alt=""></CENTER>

<ul><font size=+0>
The Swedish ABB plays an important role in the financial operations of the international ABB Group.<P>

The main objective of the Financial Services segment is to exploit as far as is possible the financial synergies in the ABB Group and to achieve a good profitability. The companies belonging to the segment offer their services under market conditions to both ABB companies and external third party clients.<P>

Within Financial Services there is an internal bank that manages liquid assets for the Swedish ABB companies, executes borrowings and foreign exchange transactions and offers consulting services.
Financial Services offers sales support for the financing of equipment supplied by ABB, and different financial packages for external third party clients. Consulting services and the arranging of the financing of projects and exports, countertrading, and asset management are other activities. In the insurance sector, Financial Services is active in financial insurance providing, for example, ABB companies with performance bonds and contract guarantees, and international reinsurance 
</font size=+1></ul><P>
 
<center>
<table border=3 cellpadding=4 cellspacing=4>
		<tr><td align=left width=140></td>
			<td align=center width=65>ABB Group</td>
			<td align=center width=65>ABB Sweden</td>

