<TITLE>ABB Transportation</TITLE>
<head><body bgcolor=#ffffff  link=#000ac5 vlink=#3a3f61 alink=#747474 text=000000# BACKGROUND="paper.gif">
<Basefont size=3>
<img src="logo.gif" vspace=12 hspace=10 align=right >
<br clear=all>
</head><br>
<img src="redline.gif"><p>
<center><img vspace=10 src="Transport.gif" alt=""></center><p>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="ABBJPG/TRAIN.JPG" HEIGHT=120 ALT=""></CENTER>

<BLOCKQUOTE><font size=+0>
In October 1995 the EU Commission approved the creation of the new company ABB Daimler-Benz Transportation (Adtranz), a merger of all the railway activities of ABB and Daimler-Benz.<p>

Adtranz Sweden manufactures electrical systems and components as well as mechanical products. The product portfolio includes rolling stock of all types like electric locomotives, multiple-unit trainsets, passenger coaches, light rail vehicles, metro cars, and people movers and AGT systems. The company can also offer total rail systems, service, maintenance and financing.<p>

Adtranz Signal develops and markets signalling and safety systems for railways. The company is a world leader in the field of automatic train control and electronic interlocking systems. 
</font size=+1></BLOCKQUOTE><P>
 
<center>
<table border=3 cellpadding=4 cellspacing=4>
		<tr><td align=left width=140></td>
			<td align=center width=65>ABB Group</td>
			<td align=center width=65>ABB Sweden</td>

		<tr><td align=left width=140>Revenues 1995 MSEK</td>
			<td align=right width=65>20 491</td>
			<td align=right width=65>3 763</td>

		<tr><td align=left width=140>Employees</td>
			<td align=right width=65>10 717</td>
			<td align=right width=65>1 798</td>
</table></center>
