<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> ABB Carbon</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"
  VLINK="#005500">
<BR>

<IMG SRC="bilder/abb.gif"ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=131,5 HEIGHT=75><BR><BR>
<H2>ABB Carbon</H2>
<IMG SRC="bilder/line.gif" WIDTH=100% HEIGHT=5>

<H2>PFBC</H2>

<STRONG>P = Pressurised</STRONG><BR>
to 16 bar by compressed air from the gas turbine<BR><BR>

<STRONG>F= Fluidised</STRONG><BR>
The bed behaves like a boiling liquid or fluid when the air flow produces sufficient pressure for bubbling, i.e. fluidisation, to occur. Hence the name.<BR><BR>

<STRONG>B= Bed</STRONG><BR>
The environment in which the coal burns. Also contains the embedded tubes of feedwater for steam generation. At full load the bed, which consists of 99% ash and 1% coal, is approx 4 meters in depth.<BR><BR>

<STRONG>C= Combined-cycle</STRONG><BR>
Power generation using a combined cycle is based on the joint use of a gas turbine and a steam turbine for extra efficiency. PFBC is the only technology using a coal-driven gas turbine. As the steam turbine generates approx. 80% of the output, and the gas turbine approx 20% of the output, this gives PFBC a 20% better efficiency rate than conventional coal-fired plants.
<BR><BR><BR>


<CENTER><STRONG>PFBC = Pressurised Fluidised Bed Combined-cycle</STRONG></CENTER>

<BR><BR>
<IMG SRC="bilder/arrowl.gif" WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=39>
Return to<A HREF="index.htm"> ABB Carbons opening page.</A>
<BR><BR>
