<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> ABB Carbon</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"
  VLINK="#005500">

<BR>
<IMG SRC="bilder/abb.gif"ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=131,5 HEIGHT=75><BR><BR>         
<H2>ABB Carbon</H2>
<IMG SRC="bilder/line.gif" WIDTH=100% HEIGHT=5>

<H2>What is PFBC ?</H2>

PFBC stands for <A HREF="PFBC1.HTM">Pressurised Fluidised Bed Combined-cycle</A>. It is a technology which has been developed within the ABB Group for the last twenty years. The PFBC technology is based on combustion of coal in a pressurised so-called fluid bed. The electricity is generated in two systems. One of them drives a steam turbine in which approx. 80% of the electricity is generated. The remaining 20% is generated in the other system, which drives a gas turbine. This ensures high efficiency, giving something like 15% lower fuel consumption than with conventional technologies.
<BR><BR> 

Prior to combustion the coal is crushed and then mixed with limestone (dolomite). The fuel is injected into the fluidised bed and burned. The temperature in the bed is kept constant at approx. 850C. The boiler is pressurised with the help of the gas turbine. The flue gas from the combustion is taken to the turbine, where it expands and drives the compressors used to pressurise the combustion air and the generator for electrical generation. 
<BR><BR>

The feedwater is converted to steam in a number of pipe coils submerged in the fluid bed. The steam is expanded in the steam turbine - where the electricity is generated - and then taken to a condenser, where the steam is condensed back to water, for reuse in the process.
<BR><BR>

In order to further improve fuel utilisation, the PFBC plant can be used for cogeneration, i.e. production of both electricity and heat.
<BR><BR>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="bilder/basic-pf.gif" WIDTH=680,625 HEIGHT=397,875></CENTER>
<CENTER><EM><A NAME="The">The Basic PFBC process</A></EM></CENTER>

<CENTER>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD rowspan=2><A HREF="PFBC4.HTM"><IMG SRC="bilder/pfbc.jpg"WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=100></A></TD><TD></TD></TR>
<TR><TD> Press <A HREF="PFBC4.HTM">here</A> for more detailed schematic. (264 Kb)</TD>
 </TR>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>


<BR><BR>
<IMG SRC="bilder/arrowl.gif" WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=39>
Return to<A HREF="index.htm"> ABB Carbons opening page.</A>
<BR><BR>
<IMG SRC="bilder/divider.gif" WIDTH=100% HEIGHT=9>
<EM><BR>

