<BR>

<CENTER><EM>The value of high efficiency</EM></CENTER>

<STRONG><A HREF=PFBC6.HTM#ash">Ash, a resource</A></STRONG>    
<BR><BR><BR>

 
<H2><A NAME="proven">PFBC is Proven</A></H2>

<UL>
<STRONG>In operation</STRONG>
<LI><A HREF="PFBC7.HTM#vrtan">Vrtan</A> PFBC Plant
<LI><A HREF="PFBC7.HTM#tidd">Tidd</A> PFBC Plant
<LI><A HREF="PFBC7.HTM#escatron">Escatron</A> PFBC Plant
<LI><A HREF="PFBC7.HTM#wakamatsu">Wakamatsu</A> PFBC Plant
</UL>

<BR>

<UL>
<STRONG>By new orders</STRONG>
<LI><A HREF="PFBC7.HTM#karita">Karita</A> PFBC Plant
<LI><A HREF="PFBC7.HTM#cottbus">Cottbus</A> PFBC Plant
</UL>


<STRONG>To be flexible</STRONG><BR><BR>

<EM><STRONG>Modularity</STRONG></EM><BR>
PFBC comes in two sizes, the P200 rated at 85-100MWe, and P800 rated at 350-425MWe. These can be built singly or in configurations for an infinite variety of plant sizes. Standard design means that the units are mutually compatible.
<BR><BR>

<EM><STRONG>Coal qualities</STRONG></EM><BR>
ABB can offer PFBC plants using any type of coal, even of very poor quality, e.g. high ash, high sulphur content.<BR><BR>

<EM><STRONG>Technical concepts</STRONG></EM><BR>
The simplicity of the process renders it flexible and easy to use in a variety of applications. PFBC can be offered for reheat/non-reheat, for example, for condensing or district heating applications.<BR><BR>


<STRONG>To be financable</STRONG><BR>
PFBC is a viable investment, not merely a technical prospect for a utility.
<BR><BR><BR>

