<BR><BR>

<H2><A NAME="Vrtan">The Vrtan plant, Stockholm, Sweden.</A></H2>

The first PFBC plant to be commissioned was a cogeneration plant for Stockholm Energy which provides 135 MW of electricity and 225 MW of district heat using two P200 units linked to a single steam turbine.<BR><BR>

Vrtan is an existing site directly adjacent to a residential area. The location of a coal plant here would have been impossible without PFBC technology (which complies with the most severe environmental requirements). The plant is now in fully commercial operation.<BR><BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>Vrtan plant data</STRONG>

