<BR><BR><BR>
<H2><A NAME="Tidd">The Tidd plant, Ohio, USA.</A></H2>

American Electric Power (AEP) selected the TIDD power plant to demonstrate the technical and commercial viability of PFBC. It involved raising efficiency and significantly reducing emissions from the 46 year old plant by retrofitting with a P200 unit provided by a joint venture between ABB and B&W. The AEP group received financial support from the US Department of Energy (DoE) Clean Coal Technology programme and from the State of Ohio Coal Development Office.<BR><BR>

The modular nature and small size of the PFBC system enabled the combustor to be constructed in workshops and then shipped to the site. The plant was successfully operated from 1991-1995, generating electricity and providing a basis for testing of sorbent utilisation and hot gas filters.<BR><BR><BR>

<STRONG>Tidd plant data</STRONG>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Owner:</TD><TD>American Electric Power (AEP)</TD></TR>
