<H2><A NAME="Escatron">The Escatron plant, Spain.</A></H2>

Empresa Nacional de Electricidad SA (ENDESA) is a state-owned utility producing about a quarter of Spains electricity from different coals, including lignite. A P200 module was used to repower an existing steam turbine at Escatron and demonstrate PFBC technology - a first step for ENDESA to incorporating PFBC in larger power plants.<BR><BR>

The Escatron unit was built by a consortium of ABB and Babcock & Wilcox Espaola. The PFBC installation at Escatron is fuelled by Aragon black lignite with an ash content of 36%, a sulphur content of 6.8% and approximately 20% moisture. Results prove that PFBC can successfully use lignite fuel: with no increase in consumption the plants output increased by over 20%.<BR><BR><BR>

