<BR><BR><BR>

<H2><A NAME="Wakamatsu">The Wakamatsu plant, Japan.</A></H2>

Under license from ABB, Ishikawajima Harima Heavy Industries (IHI) was main supplier to the Electric Power Development Company (EPDC) utility of Japan for the Wakamatsu P200 plant. Here, the conventional boiler has been replaced by a PFBC island. ABB supplied the unique gas turbine to Wakamatsu along with some other systems.<BR><BR>

Wakamatsu is an advanced repowering project which uses a re-heat steam turbine with temperatures above 590C as well as a full-flow ceramic hot gas filter. The Wakamatsu plant passed its acceptance test September 1994. The project, which is cofunded by the Ministry of International Trade and Industry (MITI), is a first step towards construction of larger PFBC plants in Japan.<BR><BR><BR>

<STRONG>Wakamatsu plant data</STRONG>
