<TR><TD></TD><TD></TD><TD></TD></TR>

<TR><TD></TD><TD>Coal type:</TD><TD>Bituminous</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Heating value:</TD><TD>24.2 - 29.0 MJ/kg, HHV</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Sulphur content:	</TD><TD>0.3% - 1.2%</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Ash content:</TD><TD>2%- 18%</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Moisture content:</TD><TD>8% - 26%</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<BR><BR><BR>

<H2><A NAME="Karita">The Karita PFBC plant, Japan</A></H2>

Kyushu Electric Power Company (KyEPCO) is one of Japans leading utilities with an installed capacity of about 15 700 MWe. The company has a long tradition of introducing advanced new technologies into their power supply system, as was confirmed by their decision in 1991 to build the worlds first 360 MWe PFBC plant (P800).<BR><BR>

The purpose of the plant is to supply electric power to the Kyushu grid on a commercial basis. The plant consists of a P800 module with a 70 MWe PFBC machine (GT140P) in combined cycle with a 290 MWe steam turbine.<BR><BR>

The plant is designed to use a range of imported low-sulphur coals, to secure flexibility in choice of alternative coal sources. It will be supplied by Ishikawajima Harima Heavy Industries, ABB Carbons licencee in Japan, together with ABB KK, and the GT140P PFBC-machine will be supplied by ABB Carbon. The plant will be commissioned in 1998/1999.<BR><BR><BR>

<STRONG>Karita plant data</STRONG>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Owner:</TD><TD>Kyushu Electric Power Company</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Site:</TD><TD>Karita, (Kyushu), Japan</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD></TD><TD></TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD></TD><TD></TD></TR>

<TR><TD></TD><TD>Plant type:</TD><TD>1 xP800, Condensing</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Gas turbine:</TD><TD>1 xGT140 P</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Net output:</TD><TD>360 MWe</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD></TD><TD></TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD></TD><TD></TD></TR>

<TR><TD></TD><TD>Coal feed system:</TD><TD>	Paste feeding</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Coal feed rate:</TD><TD>	36.4 kg/s</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Sorbent type:	</TD><TD>Limestone</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Sorbent feed rate:</TD><TD>	3.1 kg/s</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Ash flow:</TD><TD>10.2 kg/s</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Combustion temperature:</TD><TD>870C</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Steam data:</TD><TD>241 bar(a) / 566C / 566C</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Condenser pressure:</TD><TD>	0.05 bar(a)</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Ambient temperature:</TD><TD>15C</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD></TD><TD></TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD></TD><TD></TD></TR>

<TR><TD></TD><TD>Coal type:	</TD><TD>Lignite to anthracite</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Heating value:</TD><TD>	~ 26 MJ/kg, HHV</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Sulphur content:</TD><TD>< 1.0 %</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Ash content:</TD><TD>< 20 %</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Moisture content:</TD><TD>< 7 %</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<BR><BR><BR>

<H2><A NAME="Cottbus">The Cottbus plant, Germany</A></H2>

Stadtwerke Cottbus is a municipal utility in the town of Cottbus in eastern Germany. Together with the Hamburg Kommunalfinanz group, Stadtwerke Cottbus have selected PFBC technology to replace an existing coal-fired plant near the centre of the town.
The P200 plant is a cogeneration plant which, with the help of two peak load boilers, will generate up to 74 MWe and 220 MW district heat. The plant will use locally mined Lausitzer brown coal.<BR><BR>

The order was placed in April 1996. The plant will by supplied by ABB Carbon and ABB Kraftwerke AG, and will be commissioned in 1999.<BR><BR>

The plant will be owned by a project company formed for this purpose. Another specially formed company will provide operation and maintenance of the plant.
<BR><BR><BR>

<STRONG>Cottbus plant data</STRONG>
<TABLE>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Owner:</TD><TD>Stadtwerke Cottbus + Hamburger kommunalfinanz</TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Site:</TD><TD>Cottbus</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD></TD><TD></TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD></TD><TD></TD></TR>

<TR><TD></TD><TD>Plant type</TD><TD>1xP200, Combined Heat & Power</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Gas turbine</TD><TD>1xGT35P</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Steam turbine</TD><TD>	1x G32 + 1 x UEE63</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Net Output</TD><TD>	74MWe/220MWth</TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD></TD><TD></TD></TR>
<TR><TD></TD><TD></TD><TD></TD></TR>

