<BR><BR>
<A NAME="control"></A>
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=4 WIDTH=585>
<TR>
   <TD ROWSPAN=2 VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=127 HEIGHT=190><A HREF="bitmaps/cntrl_l.jpg">
                 <IMG SRC="bitmaps/cntrl_m.jpg" BORDER=0 WIDTH=125 HEIGHT=189></A></TD>
   <TD VALIGN=TOP><FONT SIZE=+2><B>S4 Industrial Robot Controller</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
   <TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=450>
<B>Platform with potential for the 21st century</B><BR>
With the S4 controller you can keep up with the developments in production technology.
The open architecture makes it possible to implement in the furure, functions wich are not known today.
The powerful self-optimizing motion control system, the open structure with VME-bus and client/server concept,
enable new functions to be added in both hardware and software as manufacturing requirements change.
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<BR><BR>
<A NAME="robware"></A>
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=4 WIDTH=585>
<TR>
   <TD ROWSPAN=2 VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=127 HEIGHT=126><A HREF="bitmaps/rware2_l.jpg">
                 <IMG SRC="bitmaps/rware_m.gif" BORDER=0 WIDTH=125 HEIGHT=124></A></TD>
   <TD VALIGN=TOP><FONT SIZE=+2><B>RobotWare</B></FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
   <TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=450>
RobotWare is a family of software products, which represent the most powerful set of robot tools available
- tools you can depend on to help you get your job done quickly and accurately.<BR>
Within the RobotWare family, there are four classes of products:<BR>
<B>BaseWare</B>. This software includes the basic operating system for the robot controller.<BR>
<B>ProcessWare</B>. These products run on the robot controller and are designed for specific process applications,
such as spot welding or arc welding.<BR>
<B>DeskWare</B>. Designed to make you more productive by unlocking the potential of your desktop PC.
You can create robot programs, train people, store important imformation and check cycle time right at your
desk, all in the familiar Windows environment.<BR>
<B>FactoryWare</B>. These tools should be used in PCs connected to robots on the factory floor to
create custom operator interfaces for work cell monitoring and supervision.
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
