                 <IMG SRC="bitmaps/apmat_m.jpg" BORDER=0 WIDTH=125 HEIGHT=125></A></TD>
   <TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=452>
Introduction of robots in these applications means that monotonous tasks and heavy lifts can be reduced at
competitive costs. In foundries the possibilities of robot based automation are far from being exhausted.
The flexibility, capability and precision in handling both delicate and heavy parts makes the industrial
robot ideal for a large number of tasks.</TD></TR>
</TABLE>

<BR><BR>
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 CELLSPACING=1 WIDTH=585>
<TR>
   <TH COLSPAN=2><FONT SIZE=+2>Packaging</FONT></TH></TR>
<TR>
   <TD ROWSPAN=2 VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=127 HEIGHT=127><A HREF="bitmaps/appac_l.jpg">
                 <IMG SRC="bitmaps/appac_m.jpg" BORDER=0 WIDTH=125 HEIGHT=125></A></TD>
   <TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=452>
The increasing need for flexibility and productivity leads the consumer goods industry to automate their
packaging lines. ABB develops flexible cells for independent system solutions or for integration into
complete systems. Goods processed are food, beverages, cosmetics, pharmaceuticals, detergents, etc.
Typical applications: Palletizing and depalletizing, box loading and unloading, picking, case loading,
machine feeding, and special applications e.g. bottle handling.<BR>
<B>Center of Excellence</B>: <A HREF="../flexible/flexlist.htm#france">ABB Flexible Automation</A>,
Troyes, France</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<BR><BR><BR>

<IMG SRC="bitmaps/ln_red_2.gif"><BR>
Contact <A HREF="mailto:webmaster@serop.abb.se"><I>Webmaster</I></A> with questions about this web.<BR>
