<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" ">
<H2>
  SwePol Link
</H2>
<P>
<I>The following Press Release was issued by SwePol Link on December 12:</I>
<P>
(Translation from Swedish)
<P>
<H2>
  ABB selected as supplier for the HVDC link to Poland
</H2>
<P>
An HVDC link is planned to be built between Sweden and Poland. ABB has been
selected as supplier. The final agreement will be signed when the permits
to build the link have been further clarified.
<P>
The DC link being planned between Sweden and Poland will connect two different
power systems, which gives mutual benefits for both countries in economic
as well as environmental terms. The whole Baltic region will benefit from
the environmental advantages.
<P>
The process to secure the necessary permits is underway. The procurement
process has been completed. ABB is the company having presented the most
attractive proposal. SwePol Link, which will own the link, has now signed
a Letter of Intent with ABB. The Letter of Intent will enable SwePol Link
to order the link during 1997, when all permits are expected to be obtained.
<P>
ABB has supplied all existing Swedish HVDC links. There is now more than
40 years of experience from these installations. The experiences concerning
reliability and environmental impact are good.
<P>
