  <HR>
<H3>
  <A NAME="order">NEW PROJECTS</A>
</H3>
<H3>
  <A HREF="l141.htm">Bakun, Malaysia</A>
</H3>
<P>
  <HR>
<H4>
  ABB Power System has been awarded three contracts for a total of four Static
  Var Compensators and one contract for a Series Capacitor installation.
</H4>
<H3>
  Virginia Power
</H3>
<H4>
  The first contract has been awarded by Virginia Power, U.S.A. for a Utility
  SVC. This has a continuous rating of 78 Mvar capacitive to 30 Mvar inductive
  with a short-time overload rating of 167 Mvar for 10 seconds. The site for
  the compensator is located on one of the islands off the North Carolina coast
  and the compensator will regulate the system voltage and eliminate phase
  voltage unbalances during normal load fluctuations in the network. The SVC
  also has a short-time overload rating to give reactive power support following
  severe disturbances and contingencies in the network. The compensator is
  planned to be in commercial operation in July 1997.
</H4>
<H3>
  Saldanha Steel
</H3>
<H4>
  The second contract is for the turnkey delivery of two Power Quality SVCs,
  awarded by Saldanha Steel, South Africa. One of the SVCs is for a rolling
  mill and has a controllable range of 0-60 Mvar. The other SVC is for an electric
  arc furnace and has a controllable range of 15 Mvar inductive to 150 Mvar
  capacitive. Both SVCs will secure the operation of the steel mill as well
  as mitigate disturbances generated by the loads. The installation will be
  completed and commissioned in 1997.
</H4>
<H3>
  Jisco
</H3>
<H4>
  The third contract, also for a Power Quality SVC, was awarded by Jisco, China.
  The main task of this compensator will be to control the voltage variations
  on the load bus and to minimize disturbances in the network. The SVC has
  a controllable range of 5 Mvar inductive to 25 Mvar capacitive and will be
  installed at the Jisco steelworks. The installation will be completed and
  commissioned in 1998.
</H4>
<H3>
  Svenska Kraftn&auml;t
</H3>
<H4>
  Svenska Kraftn&auml;t, the Swedish National Grid, has awarded ABB a turnkey
  contract for the delivery of a 400 kV series capacitor installation to Isovaara
  in the northern part of Sweden. The capacitor bank, with a total rating of
  500 Mvar, will increase the transmission capability and improve the stability
  of the intertie transmission line between Sweden and Finland. The installation
  will enter into operation in October 1997.
</H4>
<P>
  <HR>
