<H2>Facts &amp; Figures</H2>

<H4>ABB Power System has its <A HREF="headqu.htm">headquarters</A>
and its HVDC Division in <A HREF="ludvika.htm">Ludvika</A>, Sweden.
Ludvika is an important center for ABB's Power Transmission &amp;
Distribution Segment, with manufacturing of HVDC equipment, transformers,
capacitors, arresters, switchgear, current transformers etc.</H4>

<H4>The Reactive Power Compensation and Power Systems Analysis
divisions are located in <A HREF="vasteras.htm">V&auml;ster&aring;s</A>,
which is the center of ABB's Swedish operations.</H4>

<H4>ABB Power Systems has a total of around 600 employees, 460
in Ludvika and 140 in V&auml;ster&aring;s.</H4>

