<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Our products</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body BACKGROUND="paper.jpg" bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000">
<TABLE WIDTH=780 HEIGHT=1100>
<TR><TD>
<img src="logo.gif" alt="ABB - 1.1 K" width=115 height=45 align=right hspace=20>
<br><br><br>
<hr width=90% align=center>
<br><br>
<img src="experts.gif" alt="ABB REFRIGERATION AB - EXPERTS IN KEPPING COOL - 3.4 K" width=274 height=117  align=top>
<img src="food2.jpg" alt="FOOD - 10.8 K" width=183 height=244 hspace=10 vspace=10 border=1 align=right>
<p><center>
Wherever there is a need for industrial
refrigeration, there is a good chance you 
will find our systems and products.
We are active in a wide variety of fields.
Most of our customers are <BR>in the many
different branches of the food industry.
However, we are also a major supplier 
with long experience in the process and 
chemical industries. In comfort cooling,
we offer equipment for efficient air 
conditioning in every type of operation.
To ensure good overall economy, heat
recovery systems are often integrated
in our installations. Together with
sophisticated automatic controls 
techniques, this allows us to deliver
turnkey installations ensuring an optimal
return on investments for our customers.
At the same time, we are dedicated to
offering installations that are environmentally
sound. Proof of commitments lies both in
our know-how and experience with ammonia,
as well as our active work in testing
alternative refrigerants and reducing system
refrigerant charges.Advantages like these
mean that we are able to offer our customers a reliable
basis for making  long-term decisions. 
</center>

<br>
<hr width=80% align=center size=1>
<br>
<p><center><font  size=+1><b>FOODS</b></font></center>
<br>
<hr width=90% align=center size=1>

<img src="food1.jpg" alt="FOOD - 9.4 K" width=245 height=198 hspace=10 vspace=10 border=1 align=left>
<br>
<center>Cooling and freezing are the methods most
often used in food production, storage and
distribution in order to maintain high quality
right through to the consumer.<BR>
  We have a wealth of know-how and
experience in this field. The food industry is
one of our primary customer groups. We
operate in most areas of the industry <BR>and
supply installations recognized for their efficient
energy  utilization and high availability.
The benefits include not only excellent
operating economy and low life cycle costs, 
but also maximum consideration for the
environment. In certain cases, we undertake
responsibility for the refrigeration system
throughout the distribution chain, from the
factory to the retail outlet.</center>
&nbsp<br>
&nbsp<br>
<hr width=80% align=center size=1>
<br>
<p><center><font size=+1><b>CHEMICAL AND PROCESS INDUSTRIES</b></font></center>
<br><br>
<hr width=90% align=center size=1>
<center>The chemical and process industries are
further areas in which we have extensive
involvement.
  Our products<BR> cover the widest variety of
requirements, from compression, condensation 
and drying of different gases to cooling<BR>
of hydrofluric acid, temperature regulation
in pigment manufacture and general process
refrigeration.
Like these <BR>industries, we too have reliability
as a key word.
</center>
<br>
<hr width=80% align=center size=1>
<br>
<p><center><font size=+1><b>ICE RINKS</b></font></center>
<br>
<hr width=90% align=center size=1>
<img src="ice.jpg" alt="ICE RINK - 16.6 K" width=310 height=199 hspace=10 vspace=10 border=1 align=right>
<br><br><br>
<center>For a long time, we have been supplying ice
rink refrigeration <BR>systems both for sports and
leisure purposes, such as speed<BR> skating, ice 
hockey, bandy, curling and recreational skating.<BR>
Over the years, we have delivered several
hundred installations <BR>to many countries.
Indoor ice rinks are often equipped with our<BR>
heat recovery systems.</center>
<br><br><br><br>
<hr width=90% align=center size=4>
<a href="welcome.html"><h3>Back to main menu.</h3></a>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
