<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>ABB STAL COMPANY INFORMATION</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="tile.gif">

<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="logo2.gif" ALT="ABB"><BR>
<IMG SRC="abbname2.gif" ALT="ABB STAL" WIDTH=151 HEIGHT=38 ALIGN=absbottom>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<IMG SRC="bar1.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=2>
<BR clear=all>
<FONT  SIZE=+2><STRONG>C<FONT SIZE=-1>OMPANY INFORMATION</FONT></STRONG></FONT><BR>


<P><B> <IMG SRC="karta.gif" WIDTH=141 HEIGHT=185 ALIGN=RIGHT>
<FONT SIZE=+2>W</FONT>e design and deliver components and plants for power and heat production. Our products meet 
high standards of quality, efficiency and environmental performance. Our headquarters are in Finspong, a small town in the eastern part of Sweden, some two hours south of Stockholm by car. We have been in the turbine business for more than a century, with our roots in the pioneering inventions of Gustaf de Laval and the Ljungstroem brothers. Our turbines are to be found all over the world. 
<BR><BR>
Todays ABB Stal has a turnover of about USD 500 million and some 1800 employees.
</B><BR>

<BR>
<IMG SRC="bar1.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=2 ALIGN=top>
<BR>

<TABLE CELLPADDING=2 CELLSPACING=2>
<TR><TD><IMG SRC="slottet2.gif" ALT="Finspong Castle" WIDTH=117 HEIGHT=108 ALIGN=top></TD><TD><FONT  SIZE=+2><STRONG><A NAME="finspong house">Our head office -Finspong Castle</A><BR></STRONG></FONT><B><FONT  SIZE=-1>ABB Stals headquarters are located in an old manor house, Finspong Castle, dating from 1668.
It was built by the son of a famous Dutch banker and merchant, Louis de Geer, who
came to Sweden in 1627. Finspong Castle has an interior in Dutch style, while the exterior is
traditional Swedish from that period. Part of the building has been refurbished as our private museum.</FONT></B></TD></TR>

<TR><TD><FONT  SIZE=-1><I>Finspong Castle</TD><TD></TD></TR>
<TR><TD><FONT  SIZE=-1><a href="slott2hr.gif">(Load image 49 kB)<BR><BR></A></I></TD><TD></TD></TR>

<TR><TD><IMG SRC="world.gif" ALT="World map" WIDTH=113 HEIGHT=48 ALIGN=top></TD><TD><FONT  SIZE=+2><STRONG>World wide representation</STRONG></FONT><BR>
<B>ABB Stal is represented throughout the world through the <a href="http://www.abb.com">ABB Group.</a><BR>

ABB has a <A HREF="http://www.abb.ch/abbgroup/region/region.htm">global organization</A> and information network, backed up by advanced technological know-how, economies of scale in the manufacturing of parts and products, and the financial muscle to get large projects started and running. ABB can count on the accumulated operational and management expertise of more than 200,000 employees in over 100 countries worldwide. 
</B>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<CENTER><BR><IMG SRC="bar1.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=2 ALIGN=top></CENTER>

<H4>For further information about ABB STAL, contact:</H4>
<ADRESS>Inger Welander<BR>
telephone +46 122 819 49 (direct)<BR>
fax +46 122 186 84<BR>
e-mail <A HREF="mailto:inger.welander@sesta.mail.abb.com">inger.welander@sesta.mail.abb.com</A></ADRESS>
