<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>ABB STAL CEO</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="tile.gif">

<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="logo2.gif" ALT="ABB"><BR>
<IMG SRC="abbname2.gif" ALT="ABB STAL" WIDTH=151 HEIGHT=38 ALIGN=absbottom>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<IMG SRC="bar1.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=2>
<BR clear=all>
<FONT  SIZE=+2><STRONG>A<FONT SIZE=-1>BOUT THE FUTURE  A WORD FROM OUR PRESIDENT</FONT></STRONG></FONT><BR>




<P> 
<FONT SIZE=+2>"D</FONT>edicated work to develop the technology of the future breeds the need for innovation and experience.
<P>
A century in turbine technology not only makes us familiar with a wide range of steam and gas turbine applications, but also gives us profound knowledge of the needs of customers, their goals and concerns, be it in industry, utilities or in shipping.
<P>
ABB Stal is committing major efforts and resources to R&D and co-operates closely with corporate research centres within the <A HREF="http://www.abb.ch/abbgroup">ABB Group.</A> One example of the R&D work is the <A HREF="abbdle.htm">Dry Low Emission (DLE) burner</A>, developed by ABB Corporate Research and now fitted to our  <A HREF="gt10.htm">GT10</A> and <A HREF="gt35.htm">GT35</A> industrial gas turbines.<P> 
The new DLE technology reflects our commitment to the environment. ABB Stal's products contribute to a better life for thousands of people around the world by producing power and heat in the most efficient way and with low emissions.<P>

Total quality is the target of our Continuous Improvement Programme involving all employees. Everyone contributes his best efforts and knowledge to reaching this goal. We were, of course, certified according to the ISO 9001 standards since several years ago.
<P>Gas and steam turbines for industry are the main focus of our company: gas turbines up to 50 MW and steam turbines up to 100 MW. We have also accumulated considerable experience in building and servicing large steam turbines for both nuclear and fossil fired power plants in the Swedish and Finnish markets.
<P>The <A HREF="combined.htm">combined cycle</A> / cogeneration markets provide a great opportunity for turbines in our size range. The oil and gas industry requires reliable drives for compressors and pumps. Propulsion of high-speed ferries represents an emerging market and a challenge for reliable and clean gas turbines. ABB Stal has wide experience of the propulsion of large ships in the past, when the AP steam turbine machinery was a favourite among shipowners.
<P>Today, ABB Stal is well equipped to satisfy the demands of qualified customers around the world and to build on the engineering heritage from the pioneers of the past."
<BR>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="vd.gif" WIDTH=181 HEIGHT=272 VSPACE=10><BR><EM>Leif Nilsson<BR>President</EM></P>
<BR>

<BR>

