<HEAD>
<TITLE>ABB STAL UTILITY STEAM TURBINES</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="tile.gif">

<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="logo2.gif" ALT="ABB"><BR>
<IMG SRC="abbname2.gif" ALT="ABB STAL" WIDTH=151 HEIGHT=38 ALIGN=top>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<IMG SRC="bar1.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=2>
<BR clear=all><BR>
<FONT  SIZE=+2><STRONG>U<FONT SIZE=-1>TILITY STEAM TURBINES</FONT></STRONG></FONT><BR><BR>
<B><FONT SIZE=+1>ABB STAL</FONT> offers the complete range of ABB's steam turbines for large power plants to customers in the Nordic and Baltic markets. Recent experience includes a 590 MW steam turbine for the Meri-Pori coal fired power plant and a 148 MWe/346 MWth district heating steam turbine for the Vousaari combined cycle power plant, both in Finland.<P>

<table cellpadding=6>
<tr><td valign=top>
<img src="vuosas.gif" align=top width=120 height=71><br> 
<a href="vuosa.gif">Vuosaari, Finland <br>Load image 36 k</a></td><td valign=top><strong>
ABB has a full coverage of steam turbines for power station service. The turbines are built to high standards of technology and feature:
<ul>
<li>Welded rotors for optimum thermal flexibility
<li>Welded control wheel for shift of operation without stress peaks
<li>Shrink rings for maximum thermal flexibility
<li>Single bearings for exactly defined bearing loadings and stable operation
<li>Free standing last stage blades
</strong>
</ul>
</td></tr>
</table>
<p>


ABB Stal has built and delivered steam turbines up to 1100 MW for nuclear power plants in Finland and Sweden.<P></b>

<center><br><img src="bar1.gif" width=600 height=2 align=top></center>

