<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>ABB Barras Provence</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD WIDTH=460 ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=5><B>ABB Barras Provence - 
A French Company With Long-Term Experience in the Nuclear Power Business</B></FONT></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=478>
<B>At the end of 1994, ABB Atom acquired the French company Barras Provence, a well-reputed company in the field of nuclear power. Owing to its recognized PWR reactor expertise and its knowledge of the French market, Barras Provence will serve well as a complement to the other companies in the ABB Atom&#146;s Nuclear Power Business Area. ABB Atom works closely with Barras Provence.</B>
<P>
ABB Barras Provence is situated at Manosque, about 80 kilometers north of Marseille. Its employees number about 250.  The company, which has a current turnover of approximately FRF 200 million, was founded in 1962 primarily to carry out electro-mechanical installations and service for the Commissariat &agrave; l&#146;Energie Atomique (CEA) located at Cadarache, some 15 kilometers south of Manosque. The company&#146;s operations were gradually diversified to also include the design and manufacture of equipment for nuclear power plant maintenance and service as well as the design and manufacture of equipment in the fields of defense, telecommunications, and education. The company has excellent expertise in systems for the control of robots and manipulators and in equipment for use in various kinds of tough environments. Business from the nuclear power industry today accounts for 60 per cent of the turnover, and this is expected to increase considerably over the next few years.</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=478>
<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=LEFT><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="barras2.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=RIGHT><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="barras3.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
&#147;As Barras Provence is now part of the ABB Group, the prospects for ABB&#146;s nuclear power pro- ducts in France are good,&#148; says Philippe Gros-Gean, the marketing manager for international projects. &#147;Because of the special French specifications, most of the products will have to be modified. We have years of experience in how this is to be done. The reason for such adap- tation is that there is only one owner of all the commercial nuclear power plants, EDF (Electricit&eacute; de France), which places stringent demands on even small components.&#148;
<P>
Even if the French market ranks highest, Barras Provence figures on exporting its expertise more and more.
<P>
&#147;Customers in Sweden and in other countries can benefit greatly from our PWR expertise and our unique know-how in controlling robots and manipulators,&#148; says President Lars Rylander. &#147;We also have access to very advanced technology in the field of 3-D videogrammetry. As an example of our work, I can mention the design and manufacture of prototype equipment for Vattenfall Ringhals for the internal inspection of main cooling systems.&#148;</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=478>
<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=LEFT><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="barras5.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=RIGHT><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="barras4.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=478>
Intensive work is now underway at ABB Barras Provence to certify the repair of Nuclear Steam Supply Systems (NSSS) in France. Certification  will mean that the company will be able to assume total responsibility for repair projects and thereby, for example, be directly responsible to safety authorities. The ongoing work encompasses a thorough quality assurance audit as well as the formalization of the collaboration with the other companies in ABB&#146;s Nuclear Power Business Area. These companies and Barras Provence will be audited by the French authorities.<P>

&#147;The certification, &#146;Reparateur Certification&#146;, will involve a substantial expansion of our domestic market,&#148; says Lars Rylander. &#147;This, together with increases sales of products from other ABB companies as well as an increase in exports of French nuclear power technology, gives me a positive view of the future. I think that it&#146;ll be possible to double turnover within the next three years.&#148;</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="barras1.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=478>
<I>Footnote:<BR>
CEA is the national atomic energy agency in France.  Videogrammetry involves the measurement of size, shape, and position of objects in images.</I></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="linerbow.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR> 
<TD>
<A HREF="atomweb2.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="butt1.gif"></A></TD>
<TD>
<ADDRESS><A HREF="MAILTO:info@ato.abb.se"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="butt2.gif"></A></ADDRESS></TD>
<TD>
<ADDRESS><A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@ato.abb.se"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="butt3.gif"></A></ADDRESS></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
