  <TITLE>ICSD98</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#bfffff">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">IEEE International Conference on
Conduction and Breakdown in Solid Dielectrics</FONT> </H1>

<P ALIGN=CENTER></P>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">6th ICSD'98 in V&auml;ster&aring;s,
Sweden</FONT></H1>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">June 22-25, 1998</FONT></H1>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER></H1>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>First Announcement</H1>

<P><BR>
</P>

<H2>Invitation</H2>

<P>ICSD'98 at V&auml;ster&aring;s, Sweden will be the sixth in the series
of ICSD's. The previous conferences have been held in Toulouse (1983), Erlangen
(1986), Trondheim (1989), Sestri Levante (1992) and Leicester (1995). The
organising committee cordially invites you to participate in the Conference.
<BR>
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="2" CELLPADDING="0">
<TR>
<TD ROWSPAN="3"><IMG SRC="nordic.GIF" ALT="Nordic map" WIDTH="199" HEIGHT="307" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></TD>
<TD><A HREF="http://www.westnet.se/sweden">Information about Sweden</A></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD><A HREF="http://www.arosnet.se/werbeka/vasteras/vsstarte.htm">Information
about V&auml;ster&aring;s</A></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD><A HREF="http://www.vltmedia.se/webcam/webcam.html">Picture of central V&auml;ster&aring;s
right now</A></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<BR>
</P>

<H2>Scope</H2>

<P>The Conference is an interdisciplinary forum for the exchange and discussion
of ideas, research results and practical experience on properties and phenomena
in solid dielectrics exposed to electrical fields. It is aimed at physicists,
chemists, materials scientists and engineers who are engaged in research
and experimentation in this field. Typically, the conference attracts about
150 participants. <BR>
</P>

<H2>Topics</H2>

<P>The following subjects are of particular interest for ICSD'98:<BR>
</P>

<UL>
  <LI>Conduction, polarisation and space charge Phenomena, Materials, Composites,
  Bulk effects, Electrode effects, Dynamics, Field grading, Electroluminescence
  </LI>
  <LI>Ageing and breakdown Materials, Structures, Partial discharges, Accelerated
  testing, Electrical treeing, Water treeing, Special environments (outdoor,
  radiation, space) </LI>
  <LI>Functional materials Energy conversion, Transducers, Electronic circuitry,
  Biomaterials </LI>
  <LI>Theoretical and experimental methods Measurements, Diagnostics, Computational
  techniques, Statistical analysis </LI>
</UL>

<P></P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="blixt.jpeg" ALT="Thunder" WIDTH="170" HEIGHT=
"115" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></P>

<P></P>

<H2>Deadlines</H2>

<P>Submission of abstracts: 1 November 1997<BR>
Submission of papers: 1 March 1998 <BR>
</P>

