<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ABB Network Partners - the Company</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY  BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#FF0A11" VLINK="#930000">
<IMG ALIGN=Right SRC="logo.gif" WIDTH=116 HEIGHT=55 BORDER=0>

<TABLE CELLSPACING=1 CELLPADDING=0 BORDER=0>
<TR valign=top>
	<TD  height=100 WIDTH=180>
<A HREF="senete.html"><IMG SRC="netbut.JPG" WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=15 border=0></A><p>

</TD>
<TD WIDTH=500 colspan=2>&nbsp;</TD>

<TR VALIGN=TOP>
	<TD WIDTH=140></TD>
<td WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=40 colspan=2></td>

<TR VALIGN=TOP>
		<TD WIDTH=180 valign=top><IMG ALIGN=no SRC="vd.JPG" WIDTH=180 HEIGHT=115 BORDER=0><p>
<I>Erik dmansson<BR>
President </i></TD>

<td WIDTH=400 COLSPAN=3>

<FONT SIZE=+3>The power industry is in the middle <BR>
of a rapid transformation. <BR>
Utilities and network operators <BR>
are streamlining the way they do business.</FONT><P>

The current wave of deregulation means that a utility has to sharpen its products in order to remain competitive in a market that's growing tougher everyday. Network operators' efficiency levels are being scrutinized. While at the same time, customers are demanding better service from their energy suppliers.

<DD>A utility's ability to compete is determined by a better understanding of the business process and internal work processes. Having the right information at the right time can mean everything to competitiveness. Not to mention the ability to ensure reliability and efficiency in electricity supply.

<DD>Information Technology (IT) is the key element. And that's just where ABB Network Partner AB can help.<P>

<B>Panorama meets the new demands!</B><BR>
The power industry is developing and so are the needs of products and services in this big change. That's why we've changed our business concept in order to meet these needs. The result is our Panorama Concept. 

<DD>Panorama is the ABB Network Partner AB's solution for economical, efficient and reliable management of power networks. From power generation to distribution.


<DD>The concept offers integrated solutions as well as independent products for every need. The solutions are developed for all electricity customers - both for private consumers and major industries. All with one purpose, to respond to the new and greater demands for coordinated monitoring, control, protection and metering of the power process.<P>

<B>A complete supplier</B><BR>
ABB Network Partner AB in Vsters, Sweden, markets, supplies and maintains the entire Panorama concept. We have an annual turnover in excess of $130 millions with our 730 employees.

<DD>Besides our own competence, know-how and resources, we have access to the resources and expertise of over 6.000 people in our worldwide business area.

<DD>ABB Network Partner AB can deliver the world's most complete, modern and flexible monitoring, control and protection systems. Our investment in business management systems and customer service solutions brings completeness in our Panorama offerings for the needs of the power industry.<P>

<B>At the forefront of development</B><BR>
Two key systems in the global Panorama concept - S.P.I.D.E.R. and PYRAMID - are developed by ABB in V&auml;ster&aring;s, Sweden. 

<DD>Each year ABB Network Partner AB invests more than 10% of its turnover in research and product development. This investment combined with additional efforts in R&D within our business area assures Panorama's position at the forefront in one of the fastest growing branches - information technology for the power industry. <P>

<B>With long experience</B><BR>
The roots of ABB Network Partner AB go back to the turn of the century. We installed our first protection relay in 1905 and by 1925 we had a remote controlled station in operation. Down through the years we've introduced a great number of leading innovations within our business area, appreciated even from a global perspective.

<DD>Our strategy has always been to be on the cutting edge of development supplying the power industry with solutions that are both technologically advanced and cost effective.

<DD>ABB has supplied over 1.500 network control systems and tens of thousands protection relay systems to customers world-wide. Since ABB Network Partner AB is the largest supplier, we can offer an unbeatable experience for creating solutions for monitoring, control and protection of power systems.
<P>
Now, that's something you can use"
<P>&nbsp;<P></td>


<TR VALIGN=TOP>
	<TD WIDTH=140><A HREF="netcom02.html"><IMG SRC="next.JPG" WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=15 BORDER=0></A><P>
<A HREF="senete.html"><IMG SRC="front.JPG" WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=15 BORDER=0></A></TD>
<td WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=40 colspan=2>
<I>Erik dmansson<br>
President<BR>
ABB Network Partner, Vsters Sweden</I>

</td>




