<HTML>
<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
  <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
  <TITLE>ABB HVDC projects - Bakun</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">
<P>
<A NAME="DDE_LINK2"><IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif"
    alt=""> <IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" ">
<H2>
  Bakun Hydro-Electric Corporation and ABB consortium signed contract
</H2>
<H4>
  On October 2, ABB and its consortium partner Companhia &nbsp;Brasileira de
  Projetos e Obras (CBPO) of Brazil, signed the contract with the Malaysian
  customer Bakun Hydro-Electric Corporation Sdn Bhd for the construction of
  the 2400 MW hydro-electric power plant, including the associated 1300 km
  <A HREF="l1411.htm">HVDC transmission </A>at Bakun in Sarawak, Malaysia.
  <P>
  The contract was signed in Kuala Lumpur by the three parties in presence
  of the Prime Minister of Malaysia, Dr. Mahathir Mohamad, and most of his
  cabinet ministers. The project is valued at over USD 5 billion and is the
  largest ever undertaken by ABB. &nbsp;Construction is scheduled to start
  later this year.
</H4>
<P>
<IMG SRC="sk6102.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H3>
  <A HREF="l1412.htm">Main data</A>
</H3>
<H4>
  The project will utilise the vast hydro potential of Sarawak to cope with
  the increasing electricity demand in Peninsular Malaysia and Sarawak.
</H4>
<P>
<TABLE>
  <TR valign=top>
    <TD>
      <H4>
	The project has been awarded on a turnkey basis and it includes both the
	hydro-electric generating plant on the Balui river, with the dam and power
	house, and the power transmission with HVDC converters, overhead transmission
	lines and three submarine cables each rated at 500 kV, 710 MW. The project
	also includes a five-year operation and maintenance undertaking.
      </H4>
      <P>
    </TD>
    <TD>
      <CENTER>
	<IMG SRC="bakun2.jpg">
      </CENTER>
      <CENTER>
	<I>The Balui river</I>
      </CENTER>
    </TD>
  </TR>
</TABLE>
<H4>
  ABB's consortium partner for the civil works will be CBPO of Brazil, a large
  civil engineering company belonging to the Odebrecht Group. In addition,
  substantial parts of the project will be carried out by Malaysian companies
  and other groups from Asia, Latin America and Europe.
</H4>
<H4>
  Percy Barnevik, Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer of ABB,
  says: "Malaysia's energy requirements are growing rapidly as the country's
  manufacturing sector takes off and purchasing power increases. ABB is committed
  to supporting this positive development with the most advanced technology
  available for an important renewable energy source."
</H4>
<H4>
  The concrete face rockfill dam (CFRD) will be among the highest in the world
  of its type - 205 metres, and the 670-kilometre high-voltage direct-current
  submarine cable link between Sarawak and Peninsular Malaysia will be the
  world&#180;s longest. Even with such dimensions and high ratings, the Bakun
  HEP will be safe and efficient, being based on sound and proven technologies.
</H4>
<P>
<TABLE>
  <TR valign=top>
    <TD>
      <CENTER>
	<IMG SRC="bakun5.jpg"><BR>
	<I>The river Balui, where the dam will be built.</I>
      </CENTER>
    </TD>
    <TD>
      <H4>
	G&ouml;ran Lindahl, head of ABB's global Power Transmission and Distribution
	Segment and a member of the ABB Group Executive Committee, says: "This award
	is a recognition of ABB's leadership in advanced power generation and
	transmission technology. The project will bring urgently needed power to
	both Peninsular Malaysia and Sarawak, while cutting electricity losses by
	as much as half compared to conventional systems."
      </H4>
      <H3>
	Read more about:
      </H3>
      <H3>
	<A HREF="http://www.mtc.com.my/fpub/lib/bakun/content.htm?">Bakun</A> - Green
	energy for the future (issued by Economic planning unit, Malysia, Feb 96)
      </H3>
      <H3>
	<A HREF="http://www.tnb.com.my/">Tenaga Nasional Berhad (TNB) </A>- Utility
	that will receive the power from Bakun
      </H3>
      <H3>
	<A HREF="http://www.unimas.my/">Sarawak University (UNIMAS)</A>
      </H3>
      <H3>
	<A HREF="http://www.jaring.my/stb/">Sarawak Tourist Board</A>
      </H3>
    </TD>
  </TR>
</TABLE>
<P>
  <HR>
