<HTML>
<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
  <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
  <TITLE>ABB HVDC projects - Chandrapur-Padghe</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" ">
<H2>
  Chandrapur - Padghe HVDC power transmission project
</H2>
<P>
<TABLE CELLPADDING="2">
  <TR>
    <TD ROWSPAN=2>
      <IMG SRC="chandmap.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
    </TD>
    <TD>
    </TD>
  </TR>
  <TR>
    <TD VALIGN="Bottom">
      <A HREF="l1382.htm"><IMG BORDER="0" SRC="chapad1x.jpg" ALT="Photos" WIDTH="58"
	  HEIGHT="80"></A>
    </TD>
  </TR>
</TABLE>
<P>
<H4>
  The Maharashtra State Electricity Board of India (MSEB) is constructing an
  HVDC link between Chandrapur and Padghe, in the Mumbai (Bombay) area, to
  transmit bulk power of 1500 MW at a DC voltage of 500 kV. The terminals are
  being constructed by ABB of Sweden, ABB of India and Bharat Heavy Electricals
  Limited of India. The in service date is November 1997 for Pole 1 and February
  1998 for Pole 2. The HVDC link incorporates control features to stabilise
  the Maharashtra grid, increase the power flow on the existing east-west 400
  kV AC lines and minimise the total line losses. Difficulties in obtaining
  right-of-way for the 400 kV AC alternative was an additional reason for choosing
  HVDC as the environmental impact is lower.
</H4>
<P>
<H4>
  Project status December 1996
</H4>
<H4>
  The project is developing according to schedule. System engineering and equipment
  design have been completed as has manufacturing of the European equipment
  (Thyristor valves, converter transformers, control equipment HV filter
  capacitors, breakers, telecomm equipment, etc). Transportation of equipment
  to the sites in India is almost complete (Control equipment is still at sea,
  Telecomm equipment is being shipped)
</H4>
<H4>
  The civil construction at sites is proceeding well, and installation of equipment
  has started. Each site has a work forces of over 650 people.
</H4>
<P>
<H4>
  Technical Data:
</H4>
<P>
<TABLE border>
  <TR>
    <TD>
      Commissioning year:
    </TD>
    <TD>
      1997-1998
    </TD>
  </TR>
  <TR>
    <TD>
      Power rating:
    </TD>
    <TD>
      1500 MW
    </TD>
  </TR>
  <TR>
    <TD>
      DC Voltage:
    </TD>
    <TD>
      500 kV
    </TD>
  </TR>
  <TR>
    <TD>
      Length of overhead DC line:
    </TD>
    <TD>
      752 km
    </TD>
  </TR>
  <TR>
    <TD>
      Main reason for choosing HVDC:
    </TD>
    <TD>
      Network stabilisation, cost, environmental concerns.
    </TD>
  </TR>
</TABLE>
<P>
