  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
  <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
  <TITLE>ABB Power Systems - Uno Lamm HVDC Award</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" ">
<H2>
  Uno Lamm High Voltage Direct Current Award
</H2>
<H3>
  "Engineering - Accomplishment Through Imagination and Truth"
</H3>
<H4>
  The Uno Lamm High Voltage Direct Current Award was established in 1980 by
  the Power Engineering Society of the Institute of Electrical and Electronics
  Engineers, <A HREF="http://www.ieee.org/power/power.html">IEEE-PES</A>. It
  provides a means for special recognition of those outstanding engineers and
  scientists who have contributed to the advancement of the HVDC technology.
  At the invitation of the DC Transmission Subcommittee, ASEA provided the
  initial funds used to underwrite this Award. The Subcommittee has subsequently
  solicited additional funds from other organizations.
</H4>
<H4>
  The Uno Lamm HVDC Award consists of a bronze medal, an engraved certificate
  and an honorarium of one thousand dollars.
</H4>
<H4>
  The awards have been given to:
</H4>
<H4>
  1996 John Reeve<BR>
  1995 &Aring;ke Ekstr&ouml;m<BR>
  1994 Thomas E. Calverley<BR>
  1993 Donald M. Demarest<BR>
  1992 Carlos A.O. Peixoto<BR>
  1991 Birger Funke<BR>
  1990 Glenn D. Breuer<BR>
  1989 Aleksa Gavrilovic<BR>
  1987 Karl Werner Kanngieser<BR>
  1985 Narain G. Hingorani<BR>
  1983 John D. Ainsworth<BR>
  1981 Erich Uhlmann<BR>
</H4>
<P>
  <HR>
<P>
<CENTER>
  <IMG SRC="abbhand.gif" ALIGN=TOP> | <A HREF="home.htm">ABB Power Systems
  Home Page</A> | <A HREF="http://www.abb.se">ABB Sweden</A> |
</CENTER>
