<TITLE>ABB STAL DRY EMISSION BURNER</TITLE>
</HEAD>


<BODY BACKGROUND="tile.gif">


<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="logo2.gif" ALT="ABB"><BR>
<IMG SRC="abbname2.gif" ALT="ABB STAL" WIDTH=151 HEIGHT=38 ALIGN=absbottom>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<IMG SRC="bar1.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=2>
<BR clear=all>
<FONT  SIZE=+2><STRONG>D<FONT SIZE=-1>RY LOW EMISSION COMBUSTOR</FONT></STRONG></FONT><BR><BR>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="dleburnh.gif" LOWSRC="dleburnl.gif" WIDTH=355 HEIGHT=345 BORDER=1></CENTER>

<P>The double-coned EV burner, developed by ABBCorporate Research, dramatically reduces NO<sub>x</sub> emissions from a gas turbine. The burner is included as a standard component in the GT10 and GT35 combustor systems. Each Dry Low Emission (DLE) combustor incorporates up to 18 EV-burners.
<IMG SRC="dlecombh.gif" LOWSRC="dlecombl.gif" WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=106 HSPACE=15 VSPACE=15 ALIGN=left>
<P>Equipped with the DLE combustor, ABB Stal gas turbines are among the world's most environmentally friendly in their power range.

<P>
Additional benefits of gas turbines with the DLE combustor systems are that they maintain a low specific fuel consumption in combined cycle plants and do not require any supply of expensively produced water or steam.

<BR CLEAR=ALL>

<H4>For further information about the dry low emission combustor, please contact:</H4>
