<TITLE>Release 3</TITLE>
</HEAD>


<BODY BACKGROUND="tile.gif">


<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="logo2.gif" ALT="ABB"><BR>
<IMG SRC="abbname2.gif" ALT="ABB STAL" WIDTH=151 HEIGHT=38 ALIGN=absbottom>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<IMG SRC="bar1.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=2>
<BR clear=all><BR>

<font  size=+2><b>ABB GT10 cogeneration plant for Indonesia</b></font><P>

Finspong, November 5, 1996. 
P.T. ABB Energy System Indonesia (ESI) and ABB STAL AB, Sweden, have received an order for a GT10 cogeneration plant in Indonesia. The contract, worth approximately US$13 million, was placed by P.T. Wismakarya Prasetya, which is responsible for the production of power and steam in the Texmaco group of companies.<P>

Texmaco is an Indonesian group of companies active in textiles, textile machinery, as well as heavy industry.<P>
The cogeneration plant will be installed in Karawang, east of Jakarta. It will supply power and steam to other companies in the Texmaco group, the main consumer being P.T. Polysindo, a producer of polyester yarn.<P>

P.T.ABB ESI, being the local ABB main contractor, will be responsible for the heat recovery steam generator system. ABB STAL, acting as subcontractor will be responsible for the GT10 gas turbine equipment. The scope of supply also include spare parts and  training. <P>

The key success factors to secure this order for ABB were:<P>

<li>the strong local presence of ABB through P.T. ABB ESI,
<li>the strong and rapid support from ABB STAL experts in the regional organisation in Malaysia (ABB Power Generation Sdn Bhd),
<li>the importance of having one contract partner responsible for the key components and for overall optimisation and operation,
<li>very good performance compared with the competition, and 
<li>an attractive investment cost.<P>

The power plant equipment will be supplied from Sweden in August 1997 and is due to enter operation at the beginning of 1998.<P>

ABB employs over 30,000 people in Asia Pacific and Rest of Asia, and ABBs Power Generation segment employs more than 46,000 people worldwide with orders in 1995 of over US$ 10 billion. The ABB Group employs approximately 217,000 people with orders in 1995 of over US$36 billion.<P>
 

<H4>For further information please contact:</H4>
<ADRESS>Inger Welander<BR>
telephone +46 122 819 49 (direct)<BR>
fax +46 122 186 84<BR>
e-mail <A href="mailto:inger.welander@sesta.mail.abb.com">inger.welander@sesta.mail.abb.com</A></ADRESS>
