<TITLE>Release1</TITLE>
</HEAD>


<BODY BACKGROUND="tile.gif">


<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="logo2.gif" ALT="ABB"><BR>
<IMG SRC="abbname2.gif" ALT="ABB STAL" WIDTH=151 HEIGHT=38 ALIGN=absbottom>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<IMG SRC="bar1.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=2>
<BR clear=all><BR>

<font  size=+2><b>Gas turbines for high-speed ferry</b></font><br><br>

Finspong, Sweden, August 12, 1996--In the face of strong competition ABB Stal 
has received an order for two GT35 gas turbines to be used for the propulsion of 
the high-speed ferry Buquebus B60. The ferry will be built by the Spanish shipyard
E.N.Bazan in San Fernando.<P>

ABB Stal will also be responsible for supplying the ferrys automation system, 
while ABB Stal and Bazan will share the delivery of the electrical equipment.<P>

The Buquebus B60 ferry is designed for a cruising speed of 60 knots, which makes it 
the worlds fastest car/passenger ferry in regular traffic.The two gas turbines together
develop a shaft power of 34,000kW, which corresponds to about 46,000 h.p. In
addition, the gas turbine system has been developed to operate on low cost IF 30 type
of intermediate fuel oils to achieve low operating costs.<P>

When completed, the ferry will enter into regular traffic on the Buenos-Aires, Argentina-
Montevideo, Uruguay route, at the end of 1997.<P>

In 1995 ABB Stal received an order from Stena Line for four GT35 gas turbine sets
for installation in their HSS 900 high-speed ferries. Two GT35 sets for the first ferry 
were delivered in the spring of 1996, while the two sets for the second ferry are now 
under delivery.<P>

ABB Stal, which was earlier well-known under the name of STAL-LAVAL, was the worlds leading supplier of steam turbines for marine propulsion during the 1960s and 1970s. Today, the company is a member of the ABB Group and has about 2,000
employees and product portfolio comprising industrial steam and gas turbines.(End)<P>

<H4>For further information please contact:</H4>
<ADRESS>Inger Welander<BR>
telephone +46 122 819 49 (direct)<BR>
fax +46 122 186 84<BR>
e-mail <A href="mailto:inger.welander@sesta.mail.abb.com">inger.welander@sesta.mail.abb.com</A></ADRESS>
