<HEAD>
<TITLE>Release2</TITLE>
</HEAD>


<BODY BACKGROUND="tile.gif">


<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="logo2.gif" ALT="ABB"><BR>
<IMG SRC="abbname2.gif" ALT="ABB STAL" WIDTH=151 HEIGHT=38 ALIGN=absbottom>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<IMG SRC="bar1.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=2>
<BR clear=all><BR>

<font  size=+2><b>Gas turbine for Russia</b></font><P>

Finspong, Sweden, August12,1996-- ABB Stal has recently signed a contract
with VAO Zarubezhenergostroy in the city of Ryazan, south of Moscow, for 
the supply of one GT35 gas turbine (17 MW ).The turbine will be delivered to 
the new combined heat and power (CHP) plant in Ryazan, which will be built 
and commissioned in 1998 and will become the first municipally owned power 
plant in Russia.<P>

The project is being launched within the framework of a programme aimed at
supplying heat and power to the Ryazan region. The power plant is the second 
of its kind to be provided with ABBs GT35 gas turbine.This is being built to meet
the needs of Russian municipalities for electricity and district heat. The first unit is
currently being built for the city of  Electrostal in the Moscow region.<P>

Significant features of ABBs industrial gas turbine of type GT35 are its high 
efficiency, low emissions, which meet very stringent environmental standards,
and low maintenance costs. Yet another reason why the GT35 was chosen for Ryazan is that turbine components will be manufactured in Russia and about 3,000 employees
in the Power Generation, Power Transmission and Industrial and Building Systems segments. ABBs Power Generation segment employs more than 46,000 people
worldwide with an order intake in 1995 of over US$ 10 billion. The ABB Group
employs approximately 210,000 people with an order intake in 1995 of over
US$ 36 billion.(End).


<H4>For further information please contact:</H4>
