<HEAD>
<TITLE>Release 3</TITLE>
</HEAD>


<BODY BACKGROUND="tile.gif">


<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="logo2.gif" ALT="ABB"><BR>
<IMG SRC="abbname2.gif" ALT="ABB STAL" WIDTH=151 HEIGHT=38 ALIGN=absbottom>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<IMG SRC="bar1.gif" WIDTH=600 HEIGHT=2>
<BR clear=all><BR>

<font  size=+2><b>Third ABB Stal steam turbine
for Swedish utility</b></font><P>

Finspong, Sweden, August12,1996-- ABB Stal has received an order from the power 
utility Skellefte Kraft AB for yet another steam turbine. The type LT turbine, with an output of 5 MW, is a low-pressure machine. ABB Stals deliveries also include the condenser, evacuating equipment and condensate pumps.<P>

The site for the steam turbine is adjected to Hedensbyn Combined Heat and Power
(CHP) Plant in northern Sweden and the erection will start in the spring of 1997. 
The turbine is scheduled to enter into service during the late autumn of 1997.<P>

With this investment Skellefte Kraft AB, which is one of Swedens larger power 
utilities, is entering the biomass fuel market. ABB Stals steam turbine will namely 
be installed to utilise waste steam from a biomass fuel drying plant. It will supply 
the steam turbine, via a heat exchanger, with saturated steam at a pressure of 4 bar. 
This is the first time in the world that a biomass fuel drying plant is being integrated 
into a CHP plant and is being provided with an energy-recovery low-pressure steam 
turbine.<P>

There is every indication that the district heating industry in countries with a good availability of biomass fuel will show great interest in Skellefte Kraft ABs new plant(End).<P>




<H4>For further information please contact:</H4>
<ADRESS>Inger Welander<BR>
telephone +46 122 819 49 (direct)<BR>
fax +46 122 186 84<BR>
e-mail <A href="mailto:inger.welander@sesta.mail.abb.com">inger.welander@sesta.mail.abb.com</A></ADRESS>
