<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>A Company with a Mission</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>A Company with a Mission</B></FONT></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=460>
<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=LEFT><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b02im1.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
<I>The business of ABB Atom is to be an attractive, competitive, and competent supplier to the power utilities within the nuclear power area and to actively contribute to the utilities achieving their long-term commitments regarding safety, economy, and environment.</I>
<P>
ABB Atom is a knowledge-based company with more than 40 years of successful experience in the development and supply of nuclear power plants, nuclear fuel, related services, and inspection technology. More than 1,200 employees are engaged in our nuclear activities. Besides our own competence, know-how, and resources, we have access to the resources and expertise of over 3,500 people in our ABB worldwide nuclear business area.
<P>
ABB Atom is committed to maintaining competence in the field of nuclear facilities. We are engaged in several large projects for design reconstitution, plant upgrades, and plant-life extension in Sweden and in Finland. These projects, which are similar in technical complexity to designing a new plant, enable us to retain and further develop our capabilities.
<P>
ABB Atom has initiated the &#147Young Generation&#148; project that focuses on the next generation in order to secure the future development of nuclear power. It is also an additional means of transferring expertise between generations and between people.
<P>
ABB Atom has always given high priority to quality issues. We are very proud that this systematic total quality work has received official recognition in that our Nuclear Fuel Division was granted the prestigious Swedish Quality Award 1994. Since continuous improvements is one of our strategies, we will continue our endeavors to improve quality and performance for all our products.
<P>
We, the people of ABB Atom, will do our utmost to realize our mission to helping power utilities achieve safe and economical nuclear power operation. We are confident that ABB Atom will remain one of the world&#146;s leading suppliers to the nuclear power utilities.</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=460 ALIGN=RIGHT>
Stefan Olsson<BR>
President, ABB Atom</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
