<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>ABB Nuclear Power Plants</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>ABB Nuclear Power Plants</B></FONT></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b04im1.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=412>
The ABB Group offers two nuclear concepts to its customers: the boiling water reactor (BWR) technology of ABB Atom and the pressurized water reactor (PWR) technology of ABB Combustion Engineering.
<P>
ABB Atom has delivered 11 BWRs to Swedish and Finnish utilities. The scope of supply has ranged from a nuclear island to complete turnkey deliveries. ABB Combustion Engineering has supplied 17 PWRs to utilities in the U.S.A. and the Republic of Korea.<BR>
<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=Right><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b04im2.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
ABB presently has another four nuclear reactors under construction in the Republic of Korea. The <A HREF="b04list.htm">reference list</A> will give you the details.
<P>
The safety level and operation records for the ABB Atom plants have for a long time been among the best in the world. The Energy Availability Factors are shown in the diagram.
</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b04im3.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=412>
Examples of the proven design are the latest delivered ABB Atom units, Forsmark 3 and Oskarshamn 3. They were placed in operation in 1985. Their essential features are
<P>
&#128;	internal main recirculation pumps,
<P>
&#128;	fine-motion control rod drives,
<P>
&#128;	prestressed containment,
<P>
&#128;	4-train safety systems completely separated from each other.
<P>
This is the result of more than 30 years of disciplined evolution.
<P>
ABB Atom&#146;s evolutionary advanced reactor design, denoted BWR 90+, is further developed and refined in cooperation with utilities. In this way, ABB Atom continues to advance its targets and find still better ways to serve its customers while meeting the requirements of the authorities and the public.</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="linerbow.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR> 
<TD>
<A HREF="atomweb2.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="butt1.gif"></A></TD>
