<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Plant Modernization</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>Plant Modernization</B></FONT></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b07im1.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=407>
<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=Right><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b07im2.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
Plant modernization assures long-term economical and safe energy production. Part of this is to implement the changes resulting from the evolution of safety requirements.
<P>
ABB Atom was the designer and main contractor of Oskarshamn 1, the first Swedish plant placed in commercial operation in 1972. Today, ABB Atom has an important role in the extensive modernization program for this unit. The objectives are to introduce improvements in safety functions as well as to replace old components with those of modern standards.
<P>
ABB Atom is also engaged in the modernization efforts of the two Finnish plants TVO I and II, delivered in 1978 and 1980. This modernization is aimed at preventing the effects of ageing and to secure a high production capacity, for the future.
<P>
The study phase of this project has been completed and has confirmed the projected benefits of the modernization efforts. A power uprating by 15% will take place in 1998 in addition to the increase of 8% made in 1984.</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="linerbow.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR> 
