<HEAD><TITLE>Instrumentation and Control Systems</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>Instrumentation and Control Systems</B></FONT></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b08im1.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=407>
<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=Right><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b08im2.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
ABB Atom has signed strategic partnership contracts with Swedish utilities in order to modernize complete control systems in nuclear power plants. 
<P>
ABB&#146;s control system for nuclear power plants, Nuclear Advantage, is based on modern programmable technology using ABB&#146; standard platform for control systems, Advant&reg; OCS (Open Control System) with extensive applications in power and industrial plants delivered by ABB.
<P>
The benefits of Nuclear Advantage include
<P>
&#128;	modern programmable technology Advant&reg; OCS,
<P>
&#128;	over 400 years of total operational experience with modern programmable technology in nuclear power plants in Scandinavia, Europe, the Republic of Korea, and the U.S.A.,
<P>
&#128;	an ergonomic operator interface,
<P>
&#128;	long-term technology commitment facilitating step-by-step modernization,
<P>
&#128;	open control system allowing integration of specialized instrumentation systems,
<P>
&#128;	Advant Training Simulator training operators before operation.
<P>
Nuclear Advantage meets with IAEA (International Atomic Energy Agency), NRC (Nuclear Regulatory Commission), and IEC (International Electrotechnical Commission) guides and standards. ABB also has experience from licensing similar systems with the U.S. NRC.</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="linerbow.gif"></CENTER>
