<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Waste and Back-End Facilities</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>Waste and Back-End Facilities</B></FONT></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b09im1.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=407>
Since 1991, ABB Atom has delivered compact storage canisters for spent fuel to the CLAB interim storage facility through a multiyear contract with the Swedish Nuclear Fuel and Waste Management Company, SKB. ABB Atom was also heavily engaged in the design, construction, and project management of the CLAB, which was placed into operation in 1985.
<P>
The new ABB compact storage technology has almost doubled the storage capacity at CLAB. Consequently, it proved possible to postpone construction work for a new storage cavern deep down in the bedrock by several years, with subsequent savings.
<P>
ABB&#146;s spent fuel storage equipment has been delivered to many PWRs in the U.S.A., Germany, the Republic of Korea, and Sweden, as well as to BWRs in Sweden and Finland.
<P>
ABB Atom is involved in the design work of a high level encapsulation plant, and is also studying a waste back-end treatment concept for SKB comprising
<P>
&#128;	design studies for encapsulation and final disposal,
<P>
&#128;	decommissioning studies for power plants,
<P>
&#128;	canister design,
<P>
&#128;	cost calculations for the entire back-end concept.
<P>
With the Compact Mobile Solidification System, MOSS, mounted into a standard transport container, we perform solidification of low and medium level radioactive liquid waste generated by BWR and PWR plants as well as by other nuclear facilities. We have also delivered MOSS units for the client&#146;s own use, e.g. to the Borssele PWR unit in the Netherlands.
<P>
After backfitting the waste treatment plant at the Swiss M&uuml;hleberg BWR unit with a Cement Volume Reduction System, CVRS, the waste can now be pretreated in a volume reduction step followed by solidification into a cement matrix.</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="linerbow.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR> 
<TD>
<A HREF="atomweb2.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="butt1.gif"></A></TD>
<TD>
<ADDRESS><A HREF="MAILTO:info@ato.abb.se"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="butt2.gif"></A></ADDRESS></TD>
<TD>
<ADDRESS><A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@ato.abb.se"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="butt3.gif"></A></ADDRESS></TD>
