<HEAD><TITLE>Engineering and Analysis</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>Engineering and Analysis</B></FONT></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b10im1.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=407>
Advanced systems for 3-D (three-dimensional) plant modeling and 2-D (two-dimensional) CAD are available to support the design work. The 3-D plant modeling system is used with data interfaces for geometries to other similar systems.
<P>
Plant and component data-base systems have also been implemented. These were used during the design work for the proposed fifth nuclear power plant in Finland.
<P>
State-of-the-art computer codes for both BWR and PWR plant simulation are used. They cover transient events, core stability performance, accident events including severe accidents involving core meltdown, and local transients in process systems. These codes support both the design work (e.g. by calculation of loads on structures) and the safety evaluation work.
<P>
Major computer codes for safety evaluation work have been reviewed and approved by safety authorities in a number of countries including the U.S. NRC.
<P>
Plant and systems evaluations using reliability and probabilistic methods including PSA (Probabilistic Safety Analysis) are also performed. Tools for this work also include modern codes for PSA work.
<P>
Methods and tools for PSA Level 2 evaluations (probability of environmental impact) include methods for evaluating fault trees, event trees, and accident scenarios.
</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="linerbow.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR> 
<TD>
<A HREF="atomweb2.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="butt1.gif"></A></TD>
<TD>
