<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>BWR and PWR Fuel</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>BWR and PWR Fuel</B></FONT></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b12im1.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=407>
<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=Right><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b12im2.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
ABB Atom has proven to be a technical world leader of <A HREF="bwrbundl.htm">BWR fuel</A> technology, pioneering features such as
<P>
&#128;	SVEA fuel design,
<P>
&#128;	10x10 rod array,
<P>
&#128;	Alloyed Zr-liner.
<P>
The most recent (1996) fuel design, the SVEA 96+, offers exceptional performance combined with flexibility and margins. It is provided to customers in Europe and Japan through ABB Atom and in the U.S.A. and other countries through ABB Combustion Engineering Nuclear Operations.
<P>
Commercial deliveries of SVEA 100/96 started in 1988, and several reactors now operate with almost the entire core composed of this fuel.
<P>
The ABB Atom alloyed Zr-liner has completely and successfully operated in more than 30 batches of fuel, offering full PCI (Pellet Clad Interaction) resistance for very demanding operating conditions.
<P>
Using also technology and experience from its sister company, ABB Combustion Engineering Nuclear Operations, ABB Atom provides advanced <A HREF="pwrbundl.htm">PWR fuel</A> to European customers.
<P>
Different designs, such as 16x16, 17x17, and 18x18 are available. For very demanding conditions, special cladding such as the Duplex-type cladding can be provided. Full debris protection is provided by the GUARDIAN &#129; lower end fitting.</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="linerbow.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR> 
