<HEAD><TITLE>BWR Control Rods</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>BWR Control Rods</B></FONT></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b14im1.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=407>
<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=Right><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b14im2.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
ABB Atom is also a leading supplier of <A HREF="controd.htm">BWR control rods</A> with deliveries having been carried out for many years to customers in Europe, the U.S.A., and Japan.
<P>
Several types of control rods are offered, optimized for different operating conditions such as shutdown function or control cell operation. The basic design concept is a simple and sturdy cruciform structure, with the absorber material contained in holes in the wings. Absorber materials - boron carbide and hafnium - and hole geometry are chosen to optimize mechanical life.</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="linerbow.gif"></CENTER>
