<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Fuel Services</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>Fuel Services</B></FONT></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b16im1.gif"></TD><TD><IMG SRC="b16im2.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=411>
<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=Right><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b16im3.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
Highly experienced personnel, continued development of expertise, and access to modern high-tech equipment - these prerequisites result in effective work during and between overhauls. Advanced equipment and well-proven methods help save valuable reactor and service time.
<P>
&#128;	<A HREF="telesipp.htm">TELESCOPE Sipping</A>, for instance, is performed in parallel with unloading of fuel in PWRs and BWRs, thereby cutting critical path time considerably, resulting in savings for the utilities.
<P>
&#128;	Gamma scanning is a cost-saving method in accurately surveying irradiated fuel in the pool.
<P>
&#128;	Crud sampling and analysis together with fuel rod oxide measurements are good tools for knowing the plant process water chemistry and reducing the dose rate.
<P>
&#128;	Dimensional measurements are important to secure mechanical integrity of irradiated fuel rods, fuel bundles, fuel channels, and control rods.</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="linerbow.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR> 
<TD>
<A HREF="atomweb2.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="butt1.gif"></A></TD>
<TD>
<ADDRESS><A HREF="MAILTO:info@ato.abb.se"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="butt2.gif"></A></ADDRESS></TD>
<TD>
<ADDRESS><A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@ato.abb.se"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="butt3.gif"></A></ADDRESS></TD>
