<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Reactor Services</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>Reactor Services</B></FONT></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b17im1.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=407>
We are now concentrating on offering our customers large-scale total projects in the field of reactor service at the time of annual overhaul shutdowns through collaborative contracts at fixed prices spanning several years.
<P>
This form of collaboration has been under development between ABB Atom and TVO for many years.
<P>
In the field of reactor service, we have the expertise and the equipment to carry out
<P>
&#128;	service assignments for reactor vessels, control-rod drives, and main recirculation pumps,
<P>
&#128;	design, development, manufacture, and testing of tools and equipment,
<P>
&#128;	delivery of spare parts for reactor vessels, control-rod drives, and main recirculation pumps,
<P>
&#128;	inspection, damage analyses, and repairs,
<P>
&#128;	disposal of worn-out reactor components,
<P>
&#128;	creation of 3-D CAD models of reactor vessels, reactor halls, and service equipment.
<P>
Oskarshamn 1 has become a world-renowned pioneer site in the field of repair of the primary system. Projects for preparation, inspection, and repair were carried out in the drained and decontaminated reactor vessel. The pressure vessel was provided with an internal radiation shield making it possible to work inside the vessel. Repair measures were necessary regarding cracks in feedwater pipes, and in the core shroud including its support and cover.</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
