<HEAD><TITLE>Total Quality</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER VALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>Total Quality</B></FONT></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b22im1.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b22im2.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b22im3.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=407>
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=Right><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b22im4.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
For ABB Atom, Total Quality means the continuous improvement of all of our activities to satisfy and, preferably, surpass the expectations of our customers. Our Total Quality philosophy is very much a case of putting the customer in focus and, also, of empowering company employees. We conduct ongoing improvement programs that cover all areas of the company, and these pro- grams are never ending. When we are through changing, we are through.
<P>
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=Right><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b22im5.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
The main driving force for carrying out the improvement programs is an active leadership as demonstrated by all managers. We derive the input to these programs from, for example, listening to our customers, our employees, and our suppliers.
<P>
The tools used in this endeavor are surveys and interviews. The results of our efforts can be followed up by reviewing our different metrics covering, for instance, customer, employee, and supplier satisfaction.
<P>
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=Right><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="b22im6.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
Valuable independent input is also derived from business assessments according to the Swedish Quality Award. This is a tool that has been used since 1992 by the Nuclear Fuel Division and, since 1995, by the entire company. The Swedish Quality Award is very similar to the Malcolm Baldridge National Quality Award.
<P>
The evaluation criteria are as follows:
<P>
&#128;	Leadership,
<P>
&#128;	Information and Analysis,
<P>
&#128;	Strategic Planning,
<P>
&#128;	Human Resource Development and Involvement,
<P>
&#128;	Business Processes,
<P>
&#128;	Results,
<P>
&#128;	Customer Satisfaction.
<P>
Traditional basic quality issues such as product/service quality and on-time delivery will always be given top priority. That is why our metrics for these areas will always have the goal of zero defects and 100% on-time delivery. As always, we still believe in a good quality system. We will continue to maintain and develop our systems by using the valuable input from customer audits as well as from internal audits.
<P>
ABB Atom and its subsidiary, TRC, are certified according to ISO 9001.
<P>
Further, as a continuation of the quality efforts, the introduction of an environmental management system according to the international standard ISO 140001 is well in progress.</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
