<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>SVEA Fuel Benefits Forsmark</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=478>
<FONT SIZE=5><B>SVEA Fuel Benefits Forsmark</B></FONT>
<P>
<B>A high degree of availability and high power capacity - these are the primary characteristics of a power plant. In the case of ABB Atom&#146;s BWRs, anything beyond one shutdown a year for overhaul and reloading is considered obstructive downtime.</B>
<P>
One particular type of &#140;obstruction&#146; has previously occurred during the initial startup following a shutdown. The fuel must then be &#140;conditioned&#146; by increasing the load in gradual steps, a so-called PCI (Pellet Cladding Interaction) restricted startup. The purpose of this is that the fuel should adapt itself to the conditions that exist during full power.
<P>
SVEA 10x10 fuel was developed to avoid having to do this. This method of operation has now been demonstrated with a reactor core to the largest extent comprising of SVEA-96 or SVEA-100 fuel. The first reactor to have a complete 10x10 core is Oskarshamn 3, following the annual outage for &#146;96. Forsmark 2 and 3 also have chiefly SVEA-100 fuel, that is, 84% and 95% of the core, respectively.
<P>
At the time of this year&#146;s restart following fuel reloading at Forsmark 2, a power increase to 100% full reactor output (2,711 MWth, thermal output) was carried out without any fuel conditioning. The earlier wait for the accumulation of fission products, which previously was set at about 65% of output, could be dispensed with. The entire runup, after generator synchronization, to the full licensed power output of 108%, took less than 48 hours. Conventional startups, in comparison, take about four days. The production gain is estimated to equal almost 24 hours of full output.
<P>
The PCI margins remained very good throughout the entire startup phase. 
<P>
The figures below show the startup sequence and the PCI margins, continuously evaluated by the plant&#146;s core-monitoring system.
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="startup1.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
Starup sequence for Forsmark 2 after the annual outage for 1996.
<P> <BR>
<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="startup2.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
PCI margins during power increase at Forsmark 2.
</CENTER>
<P> <BR>
For further information, please get in touch with<BR>
ABB Atom<BR>
Roland Deleryd<BR>
Phone: +46 (0)21 34 77 78 (direct line)<BR>
Jan Norb&auml;ck<BR>
Phone: +46 (0)21 34 78 56 (direct line)<BR>
</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="linerbow.gif"></CENTER>
