<HEAD><TITLE>Another Belgian Fuel Order</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=478>
<KBD>
AUGUST 19, 1996<BR>
---------------<P>
<FONT SIZE=+1><B>Another Belgian Fuel Order</B>
<P>
ABB Atom has received an order for another year's supply of reload fuel for the nuclear power plant at Tihange 2 in Belgium. The order, worth about SEK 50 million, represents the exercising of an option in the present contract, which was signed in 1993, that covered three reload deliveries scheduled during the period 1994 to 1997.
<P>
The new order involves fuel to be supplied in 1998. The above contract also contains options for two additional reloads.
<P>
Tihange 2 is owned by the Electrabel power company, which owns and operates a total of seven PWR nuclear power plants, three at Tihange in southern Belgium, and four at Doel in the north.
</KBD></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
