<HEAD><TITLE>Young Communicators take action!</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=478>
<KBD>
JUNE 17, 1996<BR>
-------------<P>
<FONT SIZE=4><B>Young Communicators take action!</B>
<P>
Within the well established Young Generation organisation, a group has formed to work with information regarding energy production and the environment. The group of communicators consists of young employees from ABB Atom and the nuclear power producing companies in Sweden.
<P>
The issue of how to produce electrical power has long lasting implications on our environment and economy, thus being of profound interest for today's young Swedes. It is well known that young people and especially young women have a negative opinion of nuclear power production, and the purpose of this group of communicators is to focus on information and debate from a decidedly young perspective.
<P>
Receiving visitors at the company, giving talks at schools and organisations where young people are active, and taking an eager part in the puclic debate, the communicators will strive to relay their positive experiences from the nuclear power business and spread knowledge about nuclear power production.
<P>
The groups at the different companies involved will start out with local activities and from there draw on each other's experience to continue on a broader scale as the expected Swedish debate picks up pace during the fall of 1996.
<P>
For further information please contact:
<P>
Mr Stefan Vlachos, ABB Atom, Systems Division, +46 (0)21 34 74 90.<BR>
E-Mail <A HREF="MAILTO:atostvl@qm.ato.abb.se">atostvl@qm.ato.abb.se</A>
<P>
</KBD></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
