<HEAD><TITLE>Modernizing Oskarshamn 1 Nuclear Power Plant</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=478>
<KBD>
MAY 15, 1996<BR>
------------<P>
<FONT SIZE=4><B>Modernizing Oskarshamn 1 Nuclear Power Plant</B>
<P>
OKG AB has placed an order with ABB Atom for the modernization of the internal reactor components in Oskarshamn 1.  The project includes the replacement of the core shroud including lid and core-spray system as well as the steam separator.
<P>
This is the first time that such extensive replacement work has been carried out on the internal components of a BWR reactor.  The project is part of OKG's long-term strategy in achieving its goal with regard to safety, reliability, economy and environment.  The work is scheduled during the annual overhaul shutdown in 1997.
<P>
For ABB Atom, this order represents an important reference on the international market, taking into consideration the problems with cracks found in the internals of foreign reactors.
<P>
"We have recently completed a comprehensive re-organization with the aim of creating the best possible prerequisites for meeting customer demands with regard to the modernization of plants", says Sverre Haukeland, the head of ABB Atoms Nuclear Systems Division.  "This order from OKG, as with the earlier order regarding the modernization of the Ringhals 1 reactor, demonstrates that customers view our organization and our products with confidence."
<P>
For further information please contact:
<P>
Mr Sverre Haukeland, Vice President  and General Manager, Systems Division, +46 (0)21 - 34 72 54
<P>
S&ouml;ren Stridsberg, Process- och Mechanical Systems, Systems Division, +46 (0)21 -  34 73 29
</KBD></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
