<HEAD><TITLE>Modernizing Nuclear Power Plants at Ringhals 1</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=478>
<KBD>
MAY 10, 1996<BR>
------------<P>
<FONT SIZE=4><B>Modernizing Nuclear Power Plants at Ringhals 1</B>
<P>ABB Atom has received an order from Vattenfall AB for the modernization of the primary systems of the reactor unit at Ringhals 1.  The order comprises a complete overhaul including the replacement of pipes, connectors, and components for the main circulation system and ancillary systems.  The order is worth approximately SEK 150 million.
<P>
The modernization project is aimed at maintaining and improving safety and reliability.  It will also make future inspection work easier, thereby reducing the amount of radiation received by personnel.
<P>
The work will be carried out during the annual shutdown period in 1997.  To minimize radiation dosage levels during the work,  ABB Atom has developed an advanced remote-operated machine based on ABB's robotics.
<P>
"The order was won against stiff international competitiion, and it reinforces ABB Atom's position as the major supplier to Ringhals 1", says Sverre Haukeland, the head of ABB Atom's Nuclear Systems Division.
<P>
For further information please contact:
<P>
Mr Sverre Haukeland, Vice President  and General Manager, Systems Division, +46 (0)21 - 34 72 54
<P>
Mr Mats Olsson, General Manager, Component Service, Service Division, +46 (0)21 34 74 66</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
