<HEAD><TITLE>ABB and MGP Instruments in co-operation</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=478>
<KBD>
APRIL 30, 1996<BR>
--------------<P>
<FONT SIZE=4><B>ABB and MGP Instruments in co-operation</B>
<P>ABB Atom, Sweden and MGP Instruments, France have combined their resources for radioactivity monitoring. The agreement primarily covers Sweden and Finland.
<P>
The first application of the co-operation agreement will be radiation monitoring of the steam lines at the Barseb&auml;ck BWR units in Sweden. The spectrum analyser system gives early warning of damage to fuel. It is non-sensitive to changes in N-16 flow in the steam lines. The safety class is 1E.
<P>
This radioactivity measuring system is one example of the functions provided by the dedicated l&C system integrated in ABB's control system for Nuclear Power Plants, <I>Nuclear Advantage</I>.
<P>
Contact: Bertil Johansson, ABB Atom, S-721 63 V&auml;ster&aring;s, Sweden<BR>
Phone: +46-21-34 72 64<BR>
Fax: +46-21-34 73 18<BR>
</KBD></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
