<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Rolf Halde, new managing director at TRC</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=478>
<FONT SIZE=5><B>Rolf Halde, new managing director at ABB Tekniska R&ouml;ntgencentralen (TRC)</B></FONT><P>

<B>After only a few months as the head of Process Development at ABB Atom, Rolf Halde has now been appointed the new managing director of ABB TRC. He succeeds Per Brunzell, who decided to leave TRC at the end of 1995.</B>
<P>
<TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=LEFT><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="rolfhald.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
<P>
Rolf Halde, in the last few years, has worked with German undertakings for the international operations of Vattenfall AB. He has a sound background in nuclear power, since he also held the position of Business Area Manager for nuclear power and technical development at Vattenfall Energisystem AB. In the mid-eighties, he headed the office for plant engineering at Forsmark, and, before that, he was a project engineer for OKG involved in the CLAB and Oskarshamn-3 projects. He came to ABB Atom on 1 September, 1995. Rolf Halde is 48 years old, with a post-graduate engineering degree from Chalmers University of Technology, where he also earned a Dr. Eng. degree, majoring in chemical engineering and plant technology, in 1976.
<P>
<B>What have you managed to do in such a short time at ABB Atom?</B><BR>
&#147I have had the advantage of working in an expanding business in which the primary task has been to build up resources for important design analysis projects. These will be of major importance to both ABB Atom and TRC. It has been an exciting and interesting time, and I&#146;ll miss the opportunity of following up the results on site.
<P>
<B>What do you want to accomplish at TRC?</B><BR>
&#147TRC has had great success in its sphere of operation, non-destructive testing. In a number of instances, it is a world leader. I believe, however, that it is possible to further develop the company into a spearhead enterprise, particularly in the area of performing measurements in difficult places. And, generally, we will also focus on developing our technology, so that the testing itself won&#146;t constitute encumbrances for the customer. It&#146;s a matter of being able to measure faster, get more reliable results and, last but not least, reduce radiation exposure on the part of personnel.&#148;
<P>
Rolf did not get time to move to V&auml;ster&aring;s. He can now remain in Stockholm. He is married to Helena, who is a member of the medical faculty at a university. The family has a great leisure-time interest: travel. This is led to many long trips, since they have no children to take care of.
<P>
Running marathons is Rolf&#146;s second big avocation. He has run through quite a few over the years, the latest being the Berlin marathon in 1995. His next goal is to run the Boston marathon in April of this year.</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="linerbow.gif"></CENTER>
