<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>German PWR fuel order received by ABB Atom</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=478>
<KBD>
MARCH 18, 1996<BR>
--------------<P>
<FONT SIZE=4><B>German PWR fuel order received by ABB Atom</B>
<P>ABB Atom has received a strategic order covering uranium-fuel deliveries to the PreussenElektra operated nuclear power station Grohnde. The first delivery will take place at the end of 1997. The order's total worth is estimated at approximately SEK 200 million.
<P>
From 1992 to 1994, ABB Atom supplied Grohnde with demonstration quantities of 16x16 PWR fuel to become qualified as a reload supplier. The PWR plant, which is located about 50 kilometers south of Hannover, is owned by PreussenElektra AG and Gemeinschaftskraftwerk Weser GmbH.
<P>
&quot;The order was predated by many years of intense preparations&quot;, says Stefan Olsson, the President of ABB Atom. &quot;This is the first time that we have been entrusted with supplying reload fuel for this type of reactor in Germany, and we view the order as a strategic breakthrough. We feel ABB Atom has now further strengthened its position as an internationally successful supplier of nuclear fuel.&quot;
<P>
During the '80s, ABB Atom started to expand its export efforts in the field of nuclear fuel, and, in 1995 the export share constitutes almost 60 % of deliveries.
<P>
For further information please contact
<P>
Mr Stefan Olsson, President, +46 (0)21-34 71 00
<P>
Mr Sigvard Junkrans, Vice President and General Manager, Nuclear Fuel Division, +46 (0)21-34 79 64<BR>
</KBD></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="linerbow.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
