<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ABB Network Partner - Panorama</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY  BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#FF0A11" VLINK="#930000">
<IMG ALIGN=Right SRC="logo.gif" WIDTH=116 HEIGHT=55 BORDER=0>

<TABLE CELLSPACING=1 CELLPADDING=0 BORDER=0>
<TR valign=top>
	<TD  height=100 WIDTH=180>
<A HREF="senete.html"><IMG SRC="netbut.JPG" WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=15 border=0></A><p>

</TD>
<TD WIDTH=500 colspan=2>&nbsp;</TD>

<TR VALIGN=TOP>
	<TD WIDTH=140></TD>
<td WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=40 colspan=2></td>

<TR VALIGN=TOP>
		<TD WIDTH=180 valign=top><IMG SRC="changpic.JPG" WIDTH=180 HEIGHT=115 BORDER=0><P>
<A HREF="netpan01.html"><IMG SRC="panbut.JPG" WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=15 BORDER=0></A>
</TD>

<td WIDTH=400 COLSPAN=3>
<FONT SIZE=+3>Designed for <BR>
a changing world</FONT><P>


The power industry is in the middle of a radical transformation process: Energy Suppliers are now becoming Energy Service Companies.<BR>
New challenges are being faced. Traditional conditions are no longer fully valid. Challenges imposed by the competitiveness of the energy markets, greater environmental concern, growing cost-awareness and the proliferation of open information systems call for new innovative solutions.<P>

<B>New times, new strategies</B><BR>
Energy's new context requires new or revised strategies to confirm your position as a competitive and service-oriented power company. This includes a new corporate information strategy.
<DD>A broader view on the Information Technology strategy becomes the key to a competitive advantage. Successful implementation of this strategy must include proper support to all business units within the company. Externally, it means that business objectives can be redefined, taking into account new, integrated solutions based on information systems. <P>

<B>Panorama meets the challenge</B><BR>
Panorama is the ABB Network Partner solution for efficient and reliable management of power networks. Panorama spans the needs of the power industry. It is based on ABB's total know-how in power systems and how internal processes can be rationalized. 
<DD>Combined with our thorough understanding of business strategies for the power industry, Panorama is the  information system to rely on when managing the new conditions in an open and competitive electricity market.<P>

<B>A solution for every need</B><BR>
Panorama offers solutions for all electricity markets, in all types of power industries. From power generation, transmission and distribution companies all the way to the end-consumers, both industrial and private electricity consumers.
<DD>Our offerings include a complete range of applications for power network management as well as advanced communication solutions. System-wide, on station level and on detailed bay or unit level.
<DD>All in all, Panorama may encompass several roles in a modern power company. It can be the web that allows separate parts of the organization to work together.  It can be a competitive weapon for efficiency and security, while at the same time enhancing customer service and adhering to rules governing an electricity market. <P>

<B>A partner concept</B><BR>
Panorama provides opportunities for partnerships with other suppliers in adjacent application areas; for integration of complementary systems, products and services.
<DD>Partnerships might include computer and microprocessor manufacturers, graphical information systems suppliers, joint developments in communications, transducer equipment, control room furniture - just to name a few.<P>

In short, Panorama brings it all together.<P>
</td><P>
</table>

<center><IMG SRC="panofig.GIF" WIDTH=493 HEIGHT=357></center>

