<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ABB Network Partner - Panorama</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY  BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#FF0A11" VLINK="#930000">
<IMG ALIGN=Right SRC="logo.gif" WIDTH=116 HEIGHT=55 BORDER=0>

<TABLE CELLSPACING=1 CELLPADDING=0 BORDER=0>
<TR valign=top>
	<TD  height=100 WIDTH=180>
<A HREF="senete.html"><IMG SRC="netbut.JPG" WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=15 border=0></A><p>

</TD>
<TD WIDTH=500 colspan=2>&nbsp;</TD>

<TR VALIGN=TOP>
	<TD WIDTH=140></TD>
<td WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=40 colspan=2></td>

<TR VALIGN=TOP>
		<TD WIDTH=180 valign=top><IMG SRC="opnview.JPG" WIDTH=180 HEIGHT=115 BORDER=0><P>
<A HREF="netpan01.html"><IMG SRC="panbut.JPG" WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=15 BORDER=0></A>
</TD>

<td WIDTH=400 COLSPAN=3>
<FONT SIZE=+3>Panorama gives <BR>
an open view</FONT><P>

Panorama brings a new openness to every dimension. A system transparency that means access to the total amount of information for everyone connected.
<DD>Its open system architecture makes for easy integration with other application systems within the power company, thus protecting invested capital and ensuring that duplication of information and functions is minimized.<P>

<B>A new standard of freedom</B><BR>
The Panorama concept is built upon industry standards. This ensures complete harmony within Panorama as well as in relation to the world around it.
<DD>It also means that Panorama is constantly in tune with the evolution of international and industry standards. A worldwide resource base of experience allows unprecedented versatility.
<DD>This, in particular, is a unique feature when it comes to network management. The advantages are obvious to you as a customer: standards less expensive than tailor-made solutions. <P>

<B>A modular concept</B><BR>
Panorama is a building-block concept. This also means that you'll never block yourself off from future development.
<DD>Each module reflects functionality and brings benefits to the total structure. Panorama's standardized functionality becomes independent of the physical package, whether the format is American, European or Asian.
<DD>You select the modules you need to fit to your present requirements. When your demands grow or change, you simply replace the modules with more appropriate ones.
<DD>This means your investment is never lost. You can always make an incremental upgrade, a concent basic to the Panorama concept.<P>

<B>Integration in all directions</B><BR>
Panorama is built on state-of-the-art client/server technology and modern communications structures, to ensure total inter-operability. 
<DD>From a communications point of view, Panorama is designed for integration. Communications hardware and software are based on market standards, covering local area communication networks as well as wide area communication.
<DD>We also tailor telecommunications systems to the changing demands of an open and competitive power system environment. We provide reliable information transfer to minimize cost and intensify communication to end-consumers. <P>

<B>In pace with hardware development</B><BR>
In our business, things develop fast. The system concept shall at any time be able to use the latest hardware developments.
<DD>That is why Panorama is designed around functional modules. By being based upon software and databases, total portability for various hardware platforms is provided. <P>

<B>A fine-tuned system</B><BR>
Panorama's concept is based on distribution, coordinating all data. This ensures a functional distribution for maximum performance.
<DD>With Panorama you can tune your system regarding performance and availability. In the control center as well as in the substation. Just load the proper functional modules where they are needed.
Panorama means an open view in all directions, utilizing state-of-the-art technology.</td>

<TR VALIGN=TOP>
	<TD WIDTH=140><A HREF="netpan05.html"><IMG SRC="next.JPG" WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=15 BORDER=0></A><P>
