<HEAD>
<TITLE>ABB Network Partner - Panorama</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY  BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#FF0A11" VLINK="#930000">
<IMG ALIGN=Right SRC="logo.gif" WIDTH=116 HEIGHT=55 BORDER=0>

<TABLE CELLSPACING=1 CELLPADDING=0 BORDER=0>
<TR valign=top>
	<TD  height=100 WIDTH=180>
<A HREF="senete.html"><IMG SRC="netbut.JPG" WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=15 border=0></A><p>

</TD>
<TD WIDTH=500 colspan=2>&nbsp;</TD>

<TR VALIGN=TOP>
	<TD WIDTH=140></TD>
<td WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=40 colspan=2></td>

<TR VALIGN=TOP>
		<TD WIDTH=180 valign=top><IMG SRC="intuitiv.JPG" WIDTH=180 HEIGHT=115 BORDER=0><P>
<A HREF="netpan01.html"><IMG SRC="panbut.JPG" WIDTH=120 HEIGHT=15 BORDER=0></A>
</TD>

<td WIDTH=400 COLSPAN=3>
<FONT SIZE=+3>Panorama is <BR>
intuitive</FONT><P>

Being in perfect control means a constant knowledge of what's happening in an everchanging environment. The Panorama user is ready to act and respond - in touch with reality. 
<DD>It also means focusing on the overall goal, concentrating on the right task. Perfect control requires communication and co-operation between all parties in order to guarantee a coordinated process - everything in harmony in a changing world.<P>

<B>The user-friendly Panorama</B><BR>
All products and systems encompassed by the Panorama concept are easy to use, no matter what level the users are working at. Whether they are specialists working in a control room or consumers reading a meter window. Everything is user-friendly right on down the line.
<DD>The user interface is homogeneous and consistent at every level. In the control center. In the office. At the substation. In the field. In the home. Just one more reason why communication is so easy.<P>

<B>Communication made easy</B><BR>
Since Panorama is based on client/server technology and since international and industry standards are used, there's no risk that your system will consist of isolated islands.
<DD>Panorama makes it easy to integrate user interfaces with external systems. No matter who supplied them. They only have to conform to standards. 
<DD>Regardless of where ABB manufactures Panorama user interfaces, they are the same all over the world. Naturally, we adapt them to various languages - we focus on the user! This reduces product cost and makes training easier.
<DD>Mechanical design of our products may of course vary from market to market. But behind the shell, the functionality and the interfaces are the same.<P>

<B>A versatile tool box</B><BR>
Data can be entered at any level in the Panorama hierarchy. That's because Panorama's tools for data engineering, calculations, control, etc are fully coordinated. The concept is the same whether you work in the control center or at a substation. A big advantage for every user, no duplication of work.<P>

<B>An open system with security built-in</B><BR>
In a completely open system like Panorama, questions of availability become a priority. Not just for security reasons, but also because an open structure means that a vast amount of accessible information  has to be adapted to each user's task.
<DD>Panorama offers security and secrecy on the highest level. This includes access security schemes that help you decide just who has access to what and when.</td>

