<HEAD>

<TITLE>ABB Power Systems-Series Compensation</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">

<P>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">.
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" "> <BR>
Series Compensation (SC)
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="hq01.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><B> </CENTER></B><HR>

<P>
The use of series capacitors for compensating the inductive reactance
of long distance lines, is the most effective and economic method
of improving power transfer.<BR>
The two main reasons for incorporating series capacitors in transmission
systems are:
<UL>
<LI><B>To increse power transfer capability as a result of raising
the transient stability limit</B> 
<LI><B>To reduce transmission system losses by optimizing the
sharing of active power between parallel lines</B> <A NAME="DDE_LINK1"></A>
</UL>

<P>
<A HREF="r05.htm"><IMG SRC="grn_bull.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> SC System Technology</A>
<BR>
<A HREF="r06.htm"><IMG SRC="grn_bull.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> SC Electromechanical Design</A>
<BR>
<A HREF="r07.htm"><IMG SRC="grn_bull.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> SC References</A>
<BR>
<HR>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="abbhand.gif" ALIGN=TOP> | <A HREF="home.htm">ABB Power Systems Home Page</A>
| <A HREF="http://www.abb.se">ABB Sweden</A> | </CENTER><HR>

