<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
  <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
  <TITLE>ABB Power Systems-Power Quality</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">.
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" "> <BR>
<H2>
  Power Quality
</H2>
<P>
<CENTER>
  <IMG SRC="columb.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>
<P>
  <HR>
<H4>
  The Power Quality issue is becoming increasingly important to electrical
  utilities as well as to industrial and domestic consumers.
</H4>
<H4>
  Energy conservation efforts and the need for continuous control of certain
  industrial processes have led to an increase of electrical / electronic equipment
  and motor drives. Process automation involving the extensive use of electronic
  and digital control systems is also becoming common in modern industrial
  plants. Poor voltage waveforms, due for instance to harmonics or transients,
  low voltage or overvoltage conditions and unbalance in the network can lead
  to unnecessary and costly disruptions in production.
</H4>
<H4>
  Reactive power compensation technology is an effective, reliable and economically
  attractive means of improving voltage quality, as well as mitigating voltage
  unbalance and the propagation of harmonic currents in the supply network.
  The ABB Static Var Compensators are well established in industrial networks.
</H4>
<P>
  <HR>
<P>
<H4>
  The main reasons for incorporating SVC in distribution and industrial systems
  are:
</H4>
<UL>
  <LI>
    <B>To stabilise the voltage at the end of long lines</B>
  <LI>
    <B>To reduce reactive power consumption</B>
  <LI>
    <B>To reduce the system losses by balancing asymmetrical loads</B>
  <LI>
    <B>To decrease stresses in asynchronous machines</B>
  <LI>
    <B>To reduce voltage fluctuations, harmonics and light flicker</B>
</UL>
<P>
  <HR>
<P>
<A HREF="r20.htm"><IMG SRC="grn_bull.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> PQ Electromechanical
Design</A> <BR>
<A HREF="r21.htm"><IMG SRC="grn_bull.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> PQ References</A>
<BR>
<A HREF="r36.htm"><IMG SRC="grn_bull.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> Vad &auml;r elkvalitet?
( Only in Swedish )</A> <IMG SRC="sweflag.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> 
  <HR>
