<HEAD>
<TITLE>ABB Power Systems - Analysis Department</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant 
for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" 
alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H3><IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" "> </H3>

<CENTER>
<H1><B>Power Systems Analysis<BR></H1>
<FONT SIZE=5>Areas of Analytical Services
</FONT></B>
<BR><P>
The majority of the usual studies performed by the Power
Systems Analysis Department can be grouped into subject
areas as listed below:</CENTER>
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="hnew-7.gif" 
ALT="A picture of a power network" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=353 
HSPACE=30
VSPACE=-3000 BORDER=5 
UNITS=pixels>
<UL>
<LI><I>Power flow</I><UL>
<LI>The steady state of a power system during balanced
conditions, expressed in terms of voltages, powers, etc.</UL>
<P>
<LI><I>Reactive power compensation</I><UL>
<LI>Inventory and analytical studies concerning matters of
reactive power compensation</UL>
<P>
<LI><I>Stability</I><UL>
<LI>Synchronous or angle stability:<UL>
- Steady-state stability (usually a matter of damping)<BR>
- Transient stability (related to large disturbances)</UL>
<LI>Voltage stability
<LI>Subsynchronous resonance</UL>
<P>
<LI><I>Motor dynamics</I><UL>
<LI>Starting of electrical motors
<LI>Behaviour of electrical motor(s) at network 
disturbances</UL>
<P>
<LI><I>HVDC and SVC dynamic performance</I><UL>
<LI>High-voltage d.c. system
<LI>Static var compensator</UL>
<P>
<LI><I>Fault analysis</I><UL>
<LI>Balanced and unbalanced short circuits
<LI>Protective relay settings and co-ordination</UL>
<P>
<LI><I>Overvoltages</I><UL>
<LI>Temporary overvoltages of power-frequency or near
power-frequency nature
<LI>Switching overvoltages
<LI>Lightning overvoltages
<LI>Insulation co-ordination</UL>
</UL>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="hb02.gif" 
ALT="A picture of a power network" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=303 
HSPACE=30
VSPACE=-3000 BORDER=5 
UNITS=pixels><UL>
<P>
<LI><I>Harmonic analysis</I><UL>
<LI>Harmonic current levels, impedance and distortion
<LI>Conceptual filter arrangement</UL>
<P>
<LI><I>Saturation phenomena</I><UL>
<LI>Transformer inrush currents
<LI>Ferro-resonance</UL>
<P>
<LI><I>Miscellaneous disturbances</I><UL>
<LI>Diesel-generator disturbances due to the pulsating torque
<LI>Load-caused disturbances: Load unbalance, load 
variations, etc.</UL>
<P>
<LI><I>Reliability analysis</I><UL>
<LI>Reliability and availability calculations</UL></UL>
<P>
<BR>
<P>
The department also undertakes studies of unusual power
system subjects. One example: Relatively recently the
department performed a comprehensive computer-simulation
study of the pulse operation of the power supply system of a
stellarator (nuclear-fusion research test reactor).
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<P>
