<HEAD>
<TITLE>SIMPOW simulation & analysis software</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant 
for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H3><IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" "> </H3>
<H1><CENTER><B>SIMPOW</B></H1>

<H2><B>A Power System Simulation &amp; Analysis Software</B>
</H2>

<P>
<IMG SRC="hb04.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><IMG SRC="hb06.gif"
ALIGN="BOTTOM"><IMG SRC="hb05.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<P>
SIMPOW is a powerful simulation tool. It is used for 
analysis of electrical power systems.
<P>
The software is capable of simulating practically all 
types of dynamic phenomena in electrical power systems.<BR>
<P>
Considerable technical and mathematical expertise lies 
behind the development of SIMPOW, dating back to the 
late 1970's. Its functions are being continuously 
developed and modernised. 
<P>
SIMPOW is available for lease. Currently it is in use by 
a variety of customers.<BR>
Training courses in SIMPOW are given.
<P>
<P>
<P></CENTER>
<P>
<LH><FONT SIZE=4><B>Some advantages of SIMPOW:</FONT></B>
</LH>
<P>
<UL>
<LI>High degree of accuracy and versatility<BR>
<LI>Variable time step in dynamical simulations<BR>
<LI>Performs all conceivable types of simulations<BR>
<LI>User defined modelling<BR>
<LI>Contains models of FACTS devices
<LI>Explicit event handling<BR>
<LI>Switching between fundamental-frequency 
and instantaneous-value models<BR>
</UL>
<HR>
<P>
