<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
  <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
  <TITLE>ABB HVDC projects - Bakun, Transmission System</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">
<P>
<A NAME="DDE_LINK2"><IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif"
    alt=""> <IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" ">
<H2>
  The Bakun HVDC Transmission System
</H2>
<H4>
  The main part of the 2400 MW generated at the Bakun HEP will be transmitted
  by HVDC across Sarawak and the South China Sea to Peninsular Malaysia. The
  sea crossing of 670 km will be the longest in the world.
  <P>
  In this project, ABB Power Systems will deliver the converter stations and
  the telecommunication system. The size and other data for the converter stations
  lie well within the range of available experience.
  <P>
  Three DC poles, each rated at 710 MW, will be used for the power transmission.
  The transmission voltage will be 500 kV. This means that the world power
  and voltage records for HVDC cables currently held by the
  <A HREF="l131.htm">Baltic Cable </A>transmission will be exceeded. ABB High
  Voltage Cables in Karlskrona, Sweden has already tested a cable design meeting
  the requirements of the Bakun transmission. The total cable length of more
  than 2000 km will far exceed that of any previous project.
</H4>
<P>
<IMG SRC="bakun.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<P>
  <HR>
