</DOCHDR>
<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>PWR Fuel</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="headabba.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=5><TR>
<TD><FONT SIZE=5><B>ABB Atom PWR Fuel Assembly</B></FONT></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR>
<TD WIDTH=478>
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0 ALIGN=LEFT><TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="pwrbundl.gif"></TD>
</TR></TABLE>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>Assembly  design</B></FONT></CENTER>
<UL><LI><FONT SIZE=4><B>Removable nozzles for easy rod access</B></FONT><BR>
The removable top nozle has a unique snap-lock feature. This means that a minimum amount of force is required to separate the guide thimbles which, in turn, means easy access to the individual fuel rods. The removable bottom nozzle further simplifies fuel rod access.
<P>
<LI><FONT SIZE=4><B>Bulged joint for structural integrety</B></FONT><BR>
The top and mid grids have sleeves welded to the grids at each guide thimble location. The grid sleeves are bulged to the guide thimbles to provide a firm, secure connection.
<P>
<LI><FONT SIZE=4><B>Anti-snag grids for safer loading procedure</B></FONT><BR>
The bottom of the grids have anti-snag tabs between each rod. This facilities close passage by adjacent fuel assemblies during refueling. The bottom grid has anti-snag tabs on the top as well.
<P>
The grids also have improved corners to guard against snagging.
<P>
<LI><FONT SIZE=4><B>Debries catcher to prevent rod failure</B></FONT><BR>
Most rod failures are caused by debris fretting. A pattern of gull-wing shaped features in the debris catcher, below the active fuel, prevents debris from entering the fuel assembly. The debris catcher is integral with the lower part of the bottom grid and has no significant impact on the pressure drop.</UL></TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="linerbow.gif"></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=0><TR> 
<TD>
<A HREF="atomweb2.htm"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="butt1.gif"></A></TD>
